WEBVTT

1
00:00:25.188 --> 00:00:27.188
[a cappella group vocalizing]

2
00:00:59.105 --> 00:01:02.688
[breathing heavily]

3
00:01:04.855 --> 00:01:06.855
[dog barking on distance]

4
00:01:11.188 --> 00:01:12.271
[sighs loudly]

5
00:01:13.896 --> 00:01:15.146
[woman] I'm all set.

6
00:01:15.230 --> 00:01:17.021
And my room's all cleared out.

7
00:01:17.813 --> 00:01:19.271
Have you decided what to do with it?

8
00:01:19.355 --> 00:01:21.896
Well, I'd like to put
a treadmill in there.


9
00:01:21.980 --> 00:01:23.105
Ah. That's a great idea.

10
00:01:23.188 --> 00:01:25.396
But your mother wants to
keep it as it is.

11
00:01:25.480 --> 00:01:28.063
She's waiting for your life
to completely fall apart,


12
00:01:28.146 --> 00:01:31.271
so you'll come home and she'll
look after you until the end of her life.


13
00:01:31.355 --> 00:01:33.563
-No, no, that's not true.
-Kinda sad, Dad.


14
00:01:33.646 --> 00:01:34.855
-[Mom] Mm.
-You're telling me.


15
00:01:34.938 --> 00:01:36.105
[woman chuckles]

16
00:01:37.063 --> 00:01:39.730
Okay. I'll load up the van now.

17
00:01:44.271 --> 00:01:46.271
[pleasant music playing]

18
00:01:49.438 --> 00:01:51.230
Hey… Oh.

19
00:01:52.105 --> 00:01:53.771
No, come on, I'm smiling.

20
00:01:54.980 --> 00:01:56.313
[pruner snipping]

21
00:02:04.105 --> 00:02:05.021
Anna!

22
00:02:05.105 --> 00:02:07.021
Oh, Loredana, hi.

23
00:02:07.605 --> 00:02:10.855
Believe me, in two weeks' time
you'll be happy they're out of your hair.


24
00:02:12.938 --> 00:02:14.563
Though I know how you feel now.

25
00:02:14.646 --> 00:02:18.230
When Maya left home, and then Pietro too,
it was such an emotional time for me.


26
00:02:18.313 --> 00:02:19.271
Mm.

27
00:02:19.771 --> 00:02:20.646
Intimate.

28
00:02:20.730 --> 00:02:22.313
Yeah, yeah. Intimate.

29
00:02:22.396 --> 00:02:24.271
Times like these are intimate, yeah.

30
00:02:24.855 --> 00:02:26.771
-Yeah.
-There we go. All done now.


31
00:02:26.855 --> 00:02:31.105
But at least you'll be back soon
to watch soccer with your Dad, 'cause I…


32
00:02:31.188 --> 00:02:34.105
I mean, if I have to I will,
but I'd rather not… [chuckles]


33
00:02:34.188 --> 00:02:35.355
Yeah, Mom, I'll be back.

34
00:02:35.438 --> 00:02:36.896
-Okay.
-[Loredana] Uh, excuse me!


35
00:02:36.980 --> 00:02:39.563
But I really don't understand
why you wanna move to the city


36
00:02:39.646 --> 00:02:41.063
when it's so nice here.

37
00:02:41.646 --> 00:02:42.646
What the hell?

38
00:02:43.688 --> 00:02:44.813
-Bye now.
-[man] Bye.


39
00:02:44.896 --> 00:02:45.855
[woman] Bye, Mom.

40
00:02:50.146 --> 00:02:51.605
-Bye, Mom.
-[Mom whimpers] Aw.


41
00:02:51.688 --> 00:02:53.688
-[chuckles]
-[Dad kissing]


42
00:02:54.771 --> 00:02:55.730
Right.

43
00:02:56.771 --> 00:02:57.646
Hey! Hey!

44
00:02:57.730 --> 00:02:59.688
Uh, tomorrow I'm making lasagna.
You wanna stop by?


45
00:02:59.771 --> 00:03:00.980
CAR AND VAN RENTALS THROUGHOUT ITALY

46
00:03:01.605 --> 00:03:03.105
I'm… I'm just kidding.

47
00:03:03.188 --> 00:03:05.230
-Just kidding…
-Oh, come on. Whatever.


48
00:03:05.313 --> 00:03:07.313
[contemplative music playing]

49
00:03:07.896 --> 00:03:09.855
[engine starts]

50
00:03:09.938 --> 00:03:11.938
[pleasant music continues]

51
00:03:13.730 --> 00:03:15.688
[a cappella group vocalizing]

52
00:03:16.896 --> 00:03:18.146
[church bell tolling]

53
00:03:20.980 --> 00:03:24.063
15 MONTHS LATER

54
00:03:24.813 --> 00:03:25.980
[church bell tolling]

55
00:03:30.771 --> 00:03:32.771
[breathes deeply]

56
00:03:35.855 --> 00:03:38.146
You know, Emilio and Alessandra,

57
00:03:38.230 --> 00:03:40.646
they only call me
when they need something from me now.


58
00:03:40.730 --> 00:03:43.105
They wouldn't even show up
for their aunt's funeral.


59
00:03:43.188 --> 00:03:46.230
Mm-hmm. Ah.
She was just another old lady to them.


60
00:03:46.313 --> 00:03:48.271
They saw her three times, hardly knew her.

61
00:03:48.771 --> 00:03:50.896
Mama, I'm sorry, but she was still family.

62
00:03:52.730 --> 00:03:54.688
-Stay strong, hon.
-Carlo.


63
00:03:56.188 --> 00:03:57.355
Hi there.

64
00:03:57.438 --> 00:03:58.605
I'm so sorry.

65
00:03:59.105 --> 00:04:01.646
And it all happened so unexpectedly.

66
00:04:01.730 --> 00:04:04.480
She gulped down whiskey like a fish
for 90 years.


67
00:04:04.563 --> 00:04:06.230
She was bound to croak soon.

68
00:04:06.313 --> 00:04:07.688
Hey, Alessandra, how's she doing?

69
00:04:07.771 --> 00:04:09.396
-Haven't seen her in a while.
-Oh, yeah.


70
00:04:09.480 --> 00:04:11.313
Great, yeah. Unfortunately she was not…

71
00:04:11.396 --> 00:04:15.438
Well, she wasn't able to make it today
because she had a… a job interview.


72
00:04:15.521 --> 00:04:18.105
Oh, an interview!
That's great! What is it?


73
00:04:19.355 --> 00:04:20.896
Uh… [chuckles]

74
00:04:20.980 --> 00:04:23.688
No, she didn't tell me,
she's superstitious. [chuckles]


75
00:04:23.771 --> 00:04:25.021
Heroine dealer.

76
00:04:25.105 --> 00:04:27.355
[chuckles awkwardly]
And what about Emilio?


77
00:04:27.438 --> 00:04:30.563
He had another funeral…
more important one.


78
00:04:31.146 --> 00:04:32.230
He couldn't make it.

79
00:04:32.313 --> 00:04:34.771
-Can we please get out of here?
-Yeah, I'll catch up.


80
00:04:36.063 --> 00:04:38.188
Her doctors keep switching
her meds on her,


81
00:04:38.271 --> 00:04:40.938
so she's really been
on an emotional roller coaster.


82
00:04:41.563 --> 00:04:43.855
[laughs] Okay. See you, Anna.

83
00:04:43.938 --> 00:04:45.438
-[Anna] Ciao.
-Bye, Anna.


84
00:04:45.521 --> 00:04:48.480
-Beautiful daughter. Hold on to that one.
-[woman] Yeah, okay. See you later.


85
00:04:48.563 --> 00:04:49.855
-[Anna chuckling]
-Ciao.


86
00:04:49.938 --> 00:04:51.938
[pensive music playing]

87
00:04:54.855 --> 00:04:58.271
[Anna on phone] <i>W-W-Wait a second, okay?</i>
<i>Thanks. Thanks. Uh, listen…</i>


88
00:04:58.355 --> 00:05:00.438
<i>-You there?</i>
-[Alessandra] Yes, yes, Mom, I'm here.


89
00:05:00.521 --> 00:05:01.396
Ah, great.

90
00:05:01.480 --> 00:05:02.855
I ju-
- I just wanted to tell you

91
00:05:02.938 --> 00:05:05.938
that Dad and I can't wait to get together
and celebrate your birthday.


92
00:05:06.688 --> 00:05:07.855
[sighs] Me too.

93
00:05:07.938 --> 00:05:09.646
[Anna]<i>You know what I'm making for you?</i>

94
00:05:10.688 --> 00:05:11.896
Stuffed guinea hen.

95
00:05:12.563 --> 00:05:14.730
Mom, please, seriously.
You know I'm vegan now.


96
00:05:14.813 --> 00:05:17.105
Oh come on, honey,
it's your birthday, though!


97
00:05:17.188 --> 00:05:20.438
Okay. Whatever. Fine.
I'll see you tomorrow.


98
00:05:20.521 --> 00:05:22.271
Ale, I also just wanted to say,

99
00:05:22.813 --> 00:05:25.063
I saw your profile picture
on WhatsApp, and…


100
00:05:25.146 --> 00:05:28.063
<i>it looks a bit like an ad</i>
<i>for a Colombian brothel.</i>


101
00:05:28.563 --> 00:05:29.605
Mom! Jeez!

102
00:05:29.688 --> 00:05:32.521
No, I mean, of course it's beautiful,
because you are.


103
00:05:32.605 --> 00:05:33.938
But do you have to use that one?

104
00:05:34.021 --> 00:05:36.230
What… What the hell are you talking about?

105
00:05:36.313 --> 00:05:39.980
To be posing half naked in front
of a mirror with your mouth all…


106
00:05:40.480 --> 00:05:41.521
I mean, I don't get it.

107
00:05:41.605 --> 00:05:44.563
It looks like your lips
are being sucked out by a vacuum cleaner.


108
00:05:44.646 --> 00:05:46.105
Mm, 'kay, I'll see you tomorrow.

109
00:05:46.188 --> 00:05:47.855
So tomorrow what time are you coming?

110
00:05:47.938 --> 00:05:49.230
At 1:30?

111
00:05:49.313 --> 00:05:51.480
Can we make it noon instead? Uh…

112
00:05:51.563 --> 00:05:55.063
<i>So we can spend some time together,</i>
<i>and you can help me.</i>


113
00:05:55.146 --> 00:05:56.480
Okay, then. Okay, then.

114
00:05:56.563 --> 00:05:58.105
-Bye. See you tomorrow.
-[Anna] <i>Bye, hon.</i>


115
00:05:58.188 --> 00:06:00.938
-Bye, Mom. Bye, I have to go.
-[sputtering] Also… Honey?


116
00:06:01.021 --> 00:06:01.896
Uh…

117
00:06:02.480 --> 00:06:04.480
[whimsical music playing]

118
00:06:05.355 --> 00:06:06.480
Hi there, Emi.

119
00:06:06.563 --> 00:06:08.521
So, hon,
there's been a slight change of plans,


120
00:06:08.605 --> 00:06:12.021
because your sister said
she wants to come at noon, not 1:00.


121
00:06:12.105 --> 00:06:14.521
So, you might as well
come then, too. Right?


122
00:06:14.605 --> 00:06:18.021
Come on, so we can be together
for her birthday, it'll be wonderful.


123
00:06:18.105 --> 00:06:20.730
Honey, I'll be expecting you, okay?
So make sure you're there.


124
00:06:20.813 --> 00:06:22.230
'Kay, honey, bye now.

125
00:06:23.188 --> 00:06:25.313
THE RESISTANCE

126
00:06:25.396 --> 00:06:27.396
-[egg beating]
-[snoring]


127
00:06:27.480 --> 00:06:29.480
[classical piano music playing]

128
00:06:37.230 --> 00:06:39.563
Yeah, it was awesome,
we should totally go there again.


129
00:06:39.646 --> 00:06:42.146
-[loud dance music playing]
-[people cheering]


130
00:06:43.480 --> 00:06:45.480
[applauding, cheering]

131
00:06:52.063 --> 00:06:53.438
I love you, baby.

132
00:06:54.855 --> 00:06:56.355
HAPPY BIRTHDAY

133
00:06:56.438 --> 00:06:58.438
[classical music playing]

134
00:07:01.313 --> 00:07:03.438
-[loud dance music playing]
-[all cheering]


135
00:07:10.480 --> 00:07:11.938
THE TRUE ITALIAN ESPRESSO

136
00:07:12.021 --> 00:07:14.146
[classical music continues]

137
00:07:21.313 --> 00:07:22.396
[footwear clatters]

138
00:07:25.563 --> 00:07:26.771
[grunts, exhales]

139
00:07:28.896 --> 00:07:30.896
[birds chirping]

140
00:07:31.896 --> 00:07:34.438
[clock ticking]

141
00:07:42.355 --> 00:07:43.438
-[slams table]
-Fine.


142
00:07:43.980 --> 00:07:44.938
Cleaning up now.

143
00:07:45.021 --> 00:07:46.021
[sighs]

144
00:07:47.271 --> 00:07:48.438
[plates clatter]

145
00:07:48.521 --> 00:07:50.730
Look, Anna,
I'm not willing to sit and starve


146
00:07:50.813 --> 00:07:52.396
just because you're feeling pissy.

147
00:07:52.980 --> 00:07:55.063
-[plates clatter on table]
-No, not pissy at all.


148
00:07:55.563 --> 00:07:58.980
Come on, m-maybe they've just forgotten,
or just got home late--


149
00:07:59.063 --> 00:08:00.855
Carlo, give me a break, okay?

150
00:08:00.938 --> 00:08:03.188
Hey, they're just kids!
It's only in their nature.


151
00:08:03.271 --> 00:08:05.355
They all leave their parents eventually.

152
00:08:05.438 --> 00:08:07.771
Not to mention that
in your family's specific case,


153
00:08:07.855 --> 00:08:10.480
in all likelihood
they can't stand your company.


154
00:08:10.563 --> 00:08:12.063
Gee thanks, Mama.

155
00:08:14.271 --> 00:08:15.271
[Carlo sighs]

156
00:08:17.396 --> 00:08:21.563
[Anna] Please don't call her again.
Stop calling her. It's so humiliating.


157
00:08:21.646 --> 00:08:22.563
[sighs]

158
00:08:22.646 --> 00:08:23.938
[footsteps approaching]

159
00:08:32.313 --> 00:08:34.313
Don't… Don't act like such a baby!

160
00:08:38.855 --> 00:08:41.521
I made this cake for her,
so I'll do what I want now.


161
00:08:41.605 --> 00:08:44.646
-But what if they come later?
-No, they won't, though. Mm-mm.


162
00:08:44.730 --> 00:08:48.021
If they do show up, they can
eat out of the garbage, just like rats.


163
00:08:51.188 --> 00:08:53.105
[pleasant music playing]

164
00:08:53.730 --> 00:08:54.646
[door slams]

165
00:08:59.188 --> 00:09:01.355
-Hi.
-Hi.


166
00:09:01.980 --> 00:09:04.980
-Just waiting here for Maya.
-Ah, how nice for you.


167
00:09:05.063 --> 00:09:07.355
Oh, and your kids?
Aren't they coming for lunch now?


168
00:09:07.438 --> 00:09:08.271
What?

169
00:09:09.480 --> 00:09:12.105
[Loredana] I thought
it was Alessandra's birthday today.


170
00:09:12.188 --> 00:09:14.730
Oh yeah, impressive memory. [chuckles]

171
00:09:14.813 --> 00:09:17.563
And she's not coming to celebrate? [sighs]

172
00:09:17.646 --> 00:09:22.271
No, because she says she doesn't want me
to have to do all this cooking for her.


173
00:09:22.355 --> 00:09:25.063
She's gonna take us out somewhere.
She wants to surprise us.


174
00:09:25.146 --> 00:09:27.021
Oh. How nice!

175
00:09:27.105 --> 00:09:30.396
Well, because you know, eating at home
all the time can get a bit tiresome.


176
00:09:30.480 --> 00:09:32.271
-You know how it can be.
-[horn honking]


177
00:09:32.355 --> 00:09:33.855
Well, we like it.

178
00:09:33.938 --> 00:09:36.605
-[horn blaring]
-Hey! Hey! Hey, hey!


179
00:09:36.688 --> 00:09:38.813
You Southerners,
you really do learn how to honk


180
00:09:38.896 --> 00:09:40.771
before you even learn to walk, huh?

181
00:09:41.605 --> 00:09:43.396
[car doors closing]

182
00:09:43.480 --> 00:09:44.980
[Loredana] Hi, honey.

183
00:09:45.563 --> 00:09:49.146
Ooh! Maya must be pregnant
with another one!


184
00:09:50.313 --> 00:09:51.146
No.

185
00:09:52.605 --> 00:09:53.480
Uh, no?

186
00:09:54.188 --> 00:09:55.438
Ah, that's my bad.

187
00:09:56.438 --> 00:09:58.146
[chuckles weakly] See you.

188
00:10:00.855 --> 00:10:02.480
[chuckles]

189
00:10:02.563 --> 00:10:04.563
["Soy Infeliz" by Lola Beltran playing]

190
00:10:14.813 --> 00:10:19.605
[in Spanish]<i>♪ I'm unhappy ♪</i>

191
00:10:20.438 --> 00:10:22.605
♪ <i>Because I know you don't love me</i>…<i>♪</i>

192
00:10:22.688 --> 00:10:25.521
[in English] Hey, so where exactly
are we meeting up with Emilio?


193
00:10:25.605 --> 00:10:27.688
At a bar close to his office.

194
00:10:27.771 --> 00:10:31.271
Just a quick drink though,
because, uh, he's going to a dinner.


195
00:10:31.771 --> 00:10:34.521
Well, since we're quite close
to Alessandra's house,


196
00:10:34.605 --> 00:10:36.438
why don't we invite her?
Maybe she'll join us.


197
00:10:36.521 --> 00:10:37.605
Yeah, fat chance.

198
00:10:37.688 --> 00:10:39.105
Let's try. Why not?

199
00:10:39.188 --> 00:10:40.188
We can try.

200
00:10:40.813 --> 00:10:43.188
-[dog barking in distance]
-[phone line beeping]


201
00:10:43.688 --> 00:10:47.355
[in Spanish] <i>♪ I'm unhappy ♪</i>

202
00:10:48.605 --> 00:10:51.063
<i>♪ Because I know you don't love me… ♪</i>

203
00:10:51.146 --> 00:10:52.605
-This one?
-There she is. Right there.


204
00:10:55.480 --> 00:10:58.771
See, she's smoking! That liar!
She swore to me she quit that.


205
00:10:59.396 --> 00:11:00.855
[phone ringing]

206
00:11:01.688 --> 00:11:02.646
[disconnects call]

207
00:11:03.980 --> 00:11:06.396
-Hey, see the face she made just now?
-What face, huh?


208
00:11:06.480 --> 00:11:09.646
A face like, "God, that pain-in-the-ass
is calling again."


209
00:11:09.730 --> 00:11:12.146
-Stop with the nonsense. No.
-No?


210
00:11:12.230 --> 00:11:13.271
Whatever.

211
00:11:13.855 --> 00:11:14.813
Hey, come on.

212
00:11:14.896 --> 00:11:16.896
[phone ringing]

213
00:11:18.188 --> 00:11:19.271
[groans]

214
00:11:19.355 --> 00:11:21.438
See that? See that? See that?

215
00:11:21.521 --> 00:11:22.730
-Ah.
-See that face?


216
00:11:23.396 --> 00:11:25.313
Hi, Mom, what? 
I'm working right now.

217
00:11:26.396 --> 00:11:28.938
-Are you smoking again?
-[exhales smoke] No.


218
00:11:29.021 --> 00:11:30.646
<i>No, I'm not smoking.</i>

219
00:11:31.355 --> 00:11:32.521
Mom, what do you want?

220
00:11:32.605 --> 00:11:36.646
It's just that we, uh… we're in the area
to have a drink with your brother, so…


221
00:11:36.730 --> 00:11:38.146
-Yeah.
-Yes, but I'm wo--


222
00:11:38.230 --> 00:11:40.146
Oh, Mom. I, uh…

223
00:11:40.771 --> 00:11:42.896
I won't be able to come home
for Christmas.


224
00:11:42.980 --> 00:11:44.646
<i>I completely forgot to tell you.</i>

225
00:11:45.396 --> 00:11:47.396
-What's she saying?
-What are you saying?


226
00:11:47.480 --> 00:11:49.688
It's just that
Rocco and I are going to Paris.


227
00:11:49.771 --> 00:11:51.688
I'm sorry, Mom,
I totally forgot to tell you.


228
00:11:51.771 --> 00:11:52.938
[sighs]

229
00:11:53.021 --> 00:11:55.771
-[Carlo sighs loudly]
-[Alessandra] <i>Hello? Mom?</i>


230
00:11:56.980 --> 00:11:57.813
<i>Hey, Mom?</i>

231
00:11:59.438 --> 00:12:00.438
Let's go.

232
00:12:00.938 --> 00:12:03.813
-We're here. Uh, we could say hi, though.
-I said go.


233
00:12:03.896 --> 00:12:05.271
-Let's go.
-[engine starts]


234
00:12:05.355 --> 00:12:08.605
[in Spanish] <i>♪ I’m unhappy ♪</i>

235
00:12:09.230 --> 00:12:12.771
<i>♪ Yes, because you don't love me ♪</i>

236
00:12:12.855 --> 00:12:17.730
<i>♪ You think that I have to die ♪</i>

237
00:12:19.313 --> 00:12:23.855
<i>♪ That four drinks ♪</i>

238
00:12:23.938 --> 00:12:26.521
<i>♪ "Barman let me pay them" ♪</i>

239
00:12:26.605 --> 00:12:30.938
<i>♪ Are enough to soothe this pain ♪</i>

240
00:12:31.021 --> 00:12:33.771
[in English] So you know what puts me
in the Christmas spirit this year?


241
00:12:33.855 --> 00:12:35.813
-No.
-It's hopefulness.


242
00:12:37.021 --> 00:12:39.646
My hope that Rocco
will soon dump our daughter


243
00:12:39.730 --> 00:12:42.355
and that she'll come crawling back
begging us to comfort her.


244
00:12:42.938 --> 00:12:45.563
Ah, crawling, huh? 
Very Christmassy.

245
00:12:47.146 --> 00:12:49.355
And then she'll try to come in and…

246
00:12:49.438 --> 00:12:51.980
and you'll say to her
with your loving smile,


247
00:12:52.063 --> 00:12:54.813
"Uh, no. Darling, I'm so sorry.

248
00:12:54.896 --> 00:12:58.146
But your mom and I aren't just here
to wipe your ass for you anymore."


249
00:12:58.771 --> 00:13:00.938
Mm, maybe you'll tell her that, huh?

250
00:13:01.021 --> 00:13:02.313
[Emilio] Good evening.

251
00:13:02.396 --> 00:13:03.896
-Hey! Hello.
-Hi, darling. Hello.


252
00:13:03.980 --> 00:13:05.313
[exhales] I made it.

253
00:13:05.396 --> 00:13:06.730
Oh, here. These ones here are…

254
00:13:06.813 --> 00:13:08.980
-These ones here are ironed.
-[Emilio] Oh, thanks.


255
00:13:09.063 --> 00:13:10.355
Careful, don't crease them.

256
00:13:10.438 --> 00:13:12.188
Thanks. And these ones
are my dirty shirts.


257
00:13:12.271 --> 00:13:13.771
If you have them ready before…

258
00:13:13.855 --> 00:13:15.730
-Wednesday, that'd be perfect.
-[Anna] Yes, yes.


259
00:13:15.813 --> 00:13:17.813
And dry cleaner's
out of the question, huh?


260
00:13:18.396 --> 00:13:19.896
Yeah. With the salary I get…

261
00:13:19.980 --> 00:13:22.688
What, whining about money
to your mom and dad now?


262
00:13:22.771 --> 00:13:24.563
No, no, no. Uh, 
Azeglio is my boss.

263
00:13:24.646 --> 00:13:26.063
-These are my parents.
-[Azeglio] Good evening.


264
00:13:26.146 --> 00:13:27.771
-[parents] Good evening.
-[Azeglio] My pleasure.


265
00:13:27.855 --> 00:13:30.980
Yeah, I managed to figure that out.
Nice to meet you. Congrats on your son.


266
00:13:31.063 --> 00:13:32.146
[Anna] Oh, thank you.

267
00:13:32.230 --> 00:13:34.688
Congratulations, because it takes
two really selfless people


268
00:13:34.771 --> 00:13:37.355
not to have given him up
for adoption. [laughs]


269
00:13:37.438 --> 00:13:38.938
Am I right? [laughs]

270
00:13:39.021 --> 00:13:40.521
I'm kidding around.

271
00:13:40.605 --> 00:13:43.521
Don't drink too much, we have that
call with the Americans in an hour, okay?


272
00:13:43.605 --> 00:13:44.605
That's tonight?

273
00:13:44.688 --> 00:13:47.146
No. When I say "in one hour,"
I mean in one hour,


274
00:13:47.230 --> 00:13:48.605
but not today, tomorrow.

275
00:13:48.688 --> 00:13:49.813
Oh, okay.

276
00:13:50.355 --> 00:13:51.855
"Okay" what? It's tonight.

277
00:13:51.938 --> 00:13:53.730
Come on, wake the fuck up!
It's tonight, okay?


278
00:13:53.813 --> 00:13:55.313
-Tonight…
-Come on. Let's go.


279
00:13:55.396 --> 00:13:57.146
-Have a good evening, bye.
-[parents] Yeah.


280
00:13:57.230 --> 00:13:58.563
-[Azeglio chuckles]
-See you later.


281
00:13:58.646 --> 00:13:59.688
[Emilio sighs]

282
00:14:00.188 --> 00:14:02.188
[indistinct chatter]

283
00:14:04.188 --> 00:14:06.855
Don't worry about it, Mom.
I'm… I'm used to it by now.


284
00:14:07.688 --> 00:14:08.771
That guy there?

285
00:14:09.438 --> 00:14:11.480
No, I don't care.
I wasn't thinking of him.


286
00:14:11.563 --> 00:14:13.605
-What?
-[breathes deeply]


287
00:14:14.438 --> 00:14:15.313
No, your sister.

288
00:14:16.105 --> 00:14:17.271
What's happened to her?

289
00:14:17.813 --> 00:14:21.188
Well, she's not having Christmas
with us this year. She's going to Paris.


290
00:14:21.271 --> 00:14:22.646
Oh wow, what a bitch, huh?

291
00:14:22.730 --> 00:14:25.730
Well, I wouldn't use that word.
But that's the general idea.


292
00:14:26.980 --> 00:14:27.980
And what will you do now?

293
00:14:28.980 --> 00:14:30.396
What do you mean by that?

294
00:14:30.480 --> 00:14:33.146
I don't know.
Alessandra won't be there for Christmas.


295
00:14:33.230 --> 00:14:35.688
And I also sort of accepted
an invitation Uh…


296
00:14:35.771 --> 00:14:37.688
-Wh-- What--
-[Emilio] So I'll be gone.


297
00:14:37.771 --> 00:14:38.813
I'll see you after…

298
00:14:38.896 --> 00:14:41.313
Hey, but I'll be there,
with Mom and Grandma.


299
00:14:41.396 --> 00:14:42.813
-They care--
-[Emilio] Don't worry.


300
00:14:42.896 --> 00:14:45.980
We'll have a nice Christmas dinner
on the third, the fourth of January. Yeah?


301
00:14:46.063 --> 00:14:48.146
-What do you think?
-Where are you going?


302
00:14:48.230 --> 00:14:50.230
You heard him.
There's a conference call, and…


303
00:14:50.313 --> 00:14:51.396
I'll get the shirts.

304
00:14:51.480 --> 00:14:53.146
Uh… There.

305
00:14:53.813 --> 00:14:55.021
Bye, Mom. Bye, Dad.

306
00:14:55.105 --> 00:14:56.146
-Honey…
-[Carlo] Bye.


307
00:14:59.355 --> 00:15:00.355
[Anna] Hold on.

308
00:15:01.855 --> 00:15:03.438
So Christmas is canceled?

309
00:15:03.521 --> 00:15:05.896
So what? We'll have
a nice Christmas dinner on January third.


310
00:15:05.980 --> 00:15:07.313
Date doesn't matter, huh?

311
00:15:07.396 --> 00:15:08.855
Is Christmas in January now?

312
00:15:09.396 --> 00:15:12.105
Plus, after Christmas,
all the lamb is discounted.


313
00:15:12.188 --> 00:15:14.730
They practically
give it away, really. Yeah.


314
00:15:14.813 --> 00:15:16.605
[gentle holiday music playing]

315
00:15:16.688 --> 00:15:18.730
Well, what do you
want me to say, huh?

316
00:15:21.355 --> 00:15:23.355
[rumbling]

317
00:15:40.146 --> 00:15:42.521
-[man] Damn, you suck at this! [laughs]
-[woman] Aw, come on.


318
00:15:42.605 --> 00:15:44.605
Hey, look who's talking!
You look like a clown.


319
00:15:44.688 --> 00:15:46.896
Going out looking like that!
The hell's that sweater ?


320
00:15:47.813 --> 00:15:50.438
-Actually, I gave it to him.
-Ah.


321
00:15:50.938 --> 00:15:52.938
My dad got it
while he was in Lapland.

322
00:15:53.021 --> 00:15:54.855
Well, no, if you'd mentioned Lapland,

323
00:15:54.938 --> 00:15:57.105
I'd have said it was perfect
in that context,


324
00:15:57.188 --> 00:15:58.646
since that sweater's perfect…

325
00:15:58.730 --> 00:15:59.980
Anyway, how's your dad been?

326
00:16:00.063 --> 00:16:02.938
He's good. Well, he and his girlfriend
have been traveling a lot.


327
00:16:03.021 --> 00:16:05.521
And Carlo and Anna?
How have they been doing?


328
00:16:06.730 --> 00:16:07.980
Yeah. Mm… Well…

329
00:16:08.063 --> 00:16:10.355
I don't know. They're mad
I'm not coming back for Christmas.


330
00:16:10.438 --> 00:16:13.146
For the first time ever, I haven't
heard from them in a week, you know.


331
00:16:13.230 --> 00:16:14.063
How are they?

332
00:16:14.563 --> 00:16:17.980
-Oh, no, I haven't heard from them either.
-Oh, really?


333
00:16:18.771 --> 00:16:21.396
Well, hey, you guys, it's normal.

334
00:16:21.480 --> 00:16:23.396
Well, no. Not for them, though.

335
00:16:23.480 --> 00:16:26.063
It's never happened before.
It's not normal at all.


336
00:16:27.813 --> 00:16:29.480
-No?
-Mm.


337
00:16:30.230 --> 00:16:32.855
Yeah. Besides, I won't
be there for Christmas either.


338
00:16:33.480 --> 00:16:34.855
-Wait. You're joking.
-Well…


339
00:16:35.771 --> 00:16:36.896
You're not the only one…

340
00:16:42.688 --> 00:16:43.855
Nothing.

341
00:16:43.938 --> 00:16:45.980
Mom's not answering, neither is Dad.

342
00:16:46.063 --> 00:16:47.063
Call up Grandma.

343
00:16:49.438 --> 00:16:51.896
-[relaxing music playing]
-[phone vibrating]


344
00:16:54.896 --> 00:16:56.605
-[Grandma] Yes?
-[Alessandra on phone] <i>Hello?</i>


345
00:16:56.688 --> 00:16:58.105
Grandma? Hi, it's Ale.

346
00:16:58.188 --> 00:17:00.021
Were you still sleeping?
Am I disturbing you?


347
00:17:00.105 --> 00:17:01.980
No, no, I wasn't sleeping.

348
00:17:02.063 --> 00:17:05.105
-Yes, you're disturbing me. What is it?
-[Alessandra] <i>No. No, nothing.</i>


349
00:17:05.188 --> 00:17:07.021
Well, I'm just here with Emilio, and…

350
00:17:07.105 --> 00:17:08.730
[Grandma] <i>Yeah, who gives a shit?</i>

351
00:17:08.813 --> 00:17:10.063
Grandma! Hi!

352
00:17:10.146 --> 00:17:12.063
So listen,
what's up with Mom and Dad, huh?


353
00:17:12.146 --> 00:17:14.521
Because recently they're not calling
or answering their phone,


354
00:17:14.605 --> 00:17:16.771
and we haven't heard from them.
Are they okay?


355
00:17:16.855 --> 00:17:19.896
More than okay.
How would you feel if you were them?


356
00:17:20.688 --> 00:17:22.230
I guess old and bored?

357
00:17:22.313 --> 00:17:24.188
Hey, don't be such an idiot.

358
00:17:24.271 --> 00:17:27.146
Come on, I highly doubt they're bored,
after what just happened to them.


359
00:17:28.146 --> 00:17:30.271
Uh, but why? What just happened?

360
00:17:30.771 --> 00:17:31.938
[Grandma] <i>Oh, how odd.</i>

361
00:17:32.021 --> 00:17:33.521
They didn't tell you?

362
00:17:34.313 --> 00:17:36.563
Uh, they inherited money from Aunt Tea.

363
00:17:36.646 --> 00:17:39.563
<i>Your mom was always so good to her,</i>
<i>she really deserves it.</i>


364
00:17:41.355 --> 00:17:44.105
-Who the fuck is Aunt Tea?
-But what did they get from her?


365
00:17:44.188 --> 00:17:46.813
Oh, they didn't tell me.
It's a lot, though.


366
00:17:46.896 --> 00:17:48.063
Ciao, darlings.

367
00:17:49.313 --> 00:17:50.521
Yeah. Ciao.

368
00:17:53.188 --> 00:17:55.855
-[chuckling] What--
-Ah, that old hag from Ceccano.


369
00:17:56.896 --> 00:17:58.021
Huh?

370
00:17:58.105 --> 00:18:00.105
[joyful music playing]

371
00:18:03.063 --> 00:18:06.355
PROMETHEUS

372
00:18:08.063 --> 00:18:09.396
[phone line ringing]

373
00:18:10.521 --> 00:18:12.771
Nothing. Not responding.

374
00:18:12.855 --> 00:18:15.355
They won't answer my calls,
not my messages either…


375
00:18:15.438 --> 00:18:17.396
-What's that?
-[Emilio] My parents.


376
00:18:18.063 --> 00:18:20.896
They're usually clinging to me
like leeches, and now they're…


377
00:18:21.813 --> 00:18:24.438
Are your folks clingy, too,
like you're still a ten-year-old?


378
00:18:25.521 --> 00:18:28.813
Mm… Well, actually,
my parents died when I was 12.


379
00:18:29.646 --> 00:18:32.021
-Ah.
-I miss them terribly.


380
00:18:33.521 --> 00:18:34.563
I'm sorry.

381
00:18:37.021 --> 00:18:39.021
So you should insist. 
Keep calling them.

382
00:18:40.063 --> 00:18:42.688
-At least while they're still with you.
-[door opens]


383
00:18:47.146 --> 00:18:49.230
Did you seriously work
all night long on this?


384
00:18:49.313 --> 00:18:50.938
Finished this morning. Yeah.

385
00:18:51.021 --> 00:18:51.896
Oh.

386
00:18:51.980 --> 00:18:55.063
I think you must've passed out
around 2:00, 2:30.


387
00:18:55.146 --> 00:18:57.896
You had a nightmare,
and in that nightmare you were an idiot.


388
00:18:57.980 --> 00:18:59.855
Then you suddenly woke up… [laughs]

389
00:18:59.938 --> 00:19:02.146
…and wrote it all down,
in black and white here.


390
00:19:02.230 --> 00:19:04.188
Am I right? Huh?

391
00:19:04.271 --> 00:19:05.480
[laughs]

392
00:19:06.021 --> 00:19:08.063
You gotta redo it by tomorrow morning.

393
00:19:08.146 --> 00:19:10.313
Come on, wake the fuck up! 
Wake up, dude!

394
00:19:15.355 --> 00:19:17.521
-I can't take this much longer.
-[woman] I understand.


395
00:19:17.605 --> 00:19:19.813
If I were ever forced
into the "Emilio zone,"


396
00:19:19.896 --> 00:19:21.230
I'd cut and run too.

397
00:19:21.313 --> 00:19:24.855
-There's gotta be limits.
-What's the "Emilio zone," sorry?


398
00:19:24.938 --> 00:19:26.563
Oh, no, it's…

399
00:19:27.271 --> 00:19:29.271
It's just this dumb thing that Marzio…

400
00:19:29.896 --> 00:19:30.730
Um…

401
00:19:32.021 --> 00:19:33.855
I understand perfectly. I get it.

402
00:19:35.563 --> 00:19:36.438
[sighs]

403
00:19:36.521 --> 00:19:38.521
[a cappella song playing]

404
00:19:43.021 --> 00:19:44.021
[engine turns off]

405
00:19:46.396 --> 00:19:47.646
[Alessandra] You bastard!

406
00:19:48.146 --> 00:19:49.646
[Emilio] Oh. What do you want?

407
00:19:50.146 --> 00:19:51.188
So you lied, huh?

408
00:19:51.730 --> 00:19:54.563
"Let's go together tomorrow,
I'm gonna be working all night."


409
00:19:54.646 --> 00:19:56.813
Well so? I just finished early.
And you? What's with you?


410
00:19:56.896 --> 00:19:58.646
Well, my brother's an asshole. The usual.

411
00:19:58.730 --> 00:19:59.563
Shut up.

412
00:20:00.646 --> 00:20:01.813
Hey.

413
00:20:03.021 --> 00:20:03.896
[sighs]

414
00:20:04.563 --> 00:20:06.188
Now, I think we should make a point

415
00:20:06.271 --> 00:20:08.730
not to mention
the inheritance at all, okay?


416
00:20:08.813 --> 00:20:10.521
-Let them bring it up.
-But why?


417
00:20:10.605 --> 00:20:12.980
Otherwise, they'll know
that's why we came over.


418
00:20:14.105 --> 00:20:15.021
[Emilio exhales]

419
00:20:15.605 --> 00:20:17.313
[doorbell rings]

420
00:20:21.188 --> 00:20:22.438
-[Carlo] Oh!
-[both] Hello!


421
00:20:22.521 --> 00:20:23.855
What a surprise, huh?

422
00:20:23.938 --> 00:20:25.063
-[Emilio chuckles]
-Surprise!


423
00:20:25.146 --> 00:20:27.605
You weren't answering the phone,
so we came to track you down.


424
00:20:27.688 --> 00:20:29.771
-We wanted to see you.
-[Alessandra] You disappeared.


425
00:20:29.855 --> 00:20:30.980
-Come on!
-[Anna] Hello!


426
00:20:31.063 --> 00:20:32.021
[Alessandra] Hi, Mom!

427
00:20:32.105 --> 00:20:33.438
-[Anna] Hey.
-What were you up to?


428
00:20:33.521 --> 00:20:36.230
-Me? Oh, I was just making dinner.
-[Carlo sighs]


429
00:20:38.396 --> 00:20:40.563
And… Well, you wanna come in?

430
00:20:40.646 --> 00:20:43.021
[Emilio] We'd love to!
As long as we're not bothering you, eh?


431
00:20:43.105 --> 00:20:45.021
But of course you aren't.
Hey, come on now!


432
00:20:45.105 --> 00:20:47.230
I happen to have some wine,
I brought it for you.


433
00:20:47.313 --> 00:20:49.771
-How's that look?
-So you were able to find your way here?


434
00:20:49.855 --> 00:20:52.563
-Huh? What's that?
-You remembered the address, huh?


435
00:20:52.646 --> 00:20:53.896
-[laughing] Ah.
-Ah.


436
00:20:53.980 --> 00:20:55.855
-We got a comedian here.
-[Alessandra] Okay.


437
00:20:56.730 --> 00:20:59.480
Hey, I'm so sorry,
I really wasn't expecting you,


438
00:20:59.563 --> 00:21:01.313
so this is all I've got for you.

439
00:21:01.396 --> 00:21:03.730
Are you kidding? Come on, Mom.
That's plenty. Don't worry.


440
00:21:03.813 --> 00:21:04.813
[Anna] Well, not really.

441
00:21:04.896 --> 00:21:06.605
[Alessandra] It's so beautiful.
What is it?


442
00:21:06.688 --> 00:21:10.105
[Anna] Yes. Well, I thought
I'd cook up a nice giblet pie.


443
00:21:10.188 --> 00:21:13.313
The filling contains some browned chunks
of chicken heart meat,


444
00:21:13.396 --> 00:21:14.563
some liver, tripe, too.

445
00:21:14.646 --> 00:21:18.230
Comb of the rooster, and the wattle.

446
00:21:18.313 --> 00:21:21.271
-May I serve you?
-Yes. Yes, yes. [chuckles]


447
00:21:22.105 --> 00:21:23.480
Not a vegan anymore?

448
00:21:24.063 --> 00:21:27.313
Yes, but on special occasions,
I don't, uh… I don't…


449
00:21:27.396 --> 00:21:29.730
-Mm. Pass this to your brother.
-[Alessandra] Sure.


450
00:21:30.855 --> 00:21:33.855
Try this wine, here.
The guy from the wine shop recommended it.


451
00:21:33.938 --> 00:21:35.938
He said it won
"bottle of the year" in Abruzzo.


452
00:21:36.021 --> 00:21:37.688
Ah, is that true? [laughs]

453
00:21:37.771 --> 00:21:39.021
[Emilio] Here you go.

454
00:21:40.188 --> 00:21:41.605
How's that? How's that? Huh?

455
00:21:42.271 --> 00:21:44.063
Mm! Like a shit smear.

456
00:21:44.146 --> 00:21:47.563
[laughing] No, I'm kidding.
It's good. It's full-bodied.


457
00:21:47.646 --> 00:21:48.980
-"Full bodied."
-[Carlo] Thank you.


458
00:21:49.063 --> 00:21:51.771
-[Anna] So, how are things with Rocco now?
-Yeah, fine.


459
00:21:51.855 --> 00:21:53.105
-As usual.
-[Anna] Oh.


460
00:21:53.188 --> 00:21:55.646
And have you been thinking about adding a…

461
00:21:55.730 --> 00:21:58.063
Well, something to make it less "usual"?

462
00:21:58.146 --> 00:22:01.063
Come on, you know Alessandra can't
stand talking about these things, Anna.


463
00:22:01.146 --> 00:22:02.938
No, no, no, no, Dad. It's fine. No.

464
00:22:03.021 --> 00:22:07.230
I'm open. I… I actually enjoy discussing
this kind of… these topics with you.


465
00:22:07.313 --> 00:22:12.105
Although, having children, ooh,
can be so expensive now. You know?


466
00:22:14.438 --> 00:22:15.980
Very costly, no?

467
00:22:16.063 --> 00:22:18.813
-[Anna] Mm.
-Oh, and, Emilio, uh, what're you up to?


468
00:22:18.896 --> 00:22:22.146
-Me? I work, work, work, wo--
-Mm.


469
00:22:22.230 --> 00:22:24.146
But I'm not all that happy there.

470
00:22:24.688 --> 00:22:27.230
-But one has to pay the bills somehow.
-[Alessandra] Mm.


471
00:22:27.313 --> 00:22:28.396
[Carlo laughs]

472
00:22:28.480 --> 00:22:31.855
-Since money doesn't grow on trees, huh?
-[sighs] No, it doesn't.


473
00:22:37.855 --> 00:22:39.646
And how have you been? Hmm?

474
00:22:39.730 --> 00:22:41.938
-Good. We've been really great.
-Mm-hmm.


475
00:22:42.563 --> 00:22:43.896
Fine as usual.

476
00:22:49.396 --> 00:22:51.521
