537
00:25:20.313 --> 00:25:21.396
-[Alessandra] Stop!
-Shut up!


538
00:25:21.480 --> 00:25:23.855
<i>♪ We get it almost every night ♪</i>

539
00:25:25.021 --> 00:25:28.355
<i>♪ When that moon is big and bright ♪</i>

540
00:25:28.438 --> 00:25:32.271
<i>♪ It's a supernatural delight ♪</i>

541
00:25:32.355 --> 00:25:37.396
<i>♪ Everybody's dancin' in the moonlight… ♪</i>

542
00:25:40.063 --> 00:25:42.021
[bottles hissing open]

543
00:25:43.230 --> 00:25:44.480
To six million.

544
00:25:45.188 --> 00:25:46.313
[Rocco] Not bad, huh?

545
00:25:46.855 --> 00:25:49.980
Do you realize I'll be able to say goodbye
to this shitty life of mine!


546
00:25:51.938 --> 00:25:53.563
You mean your life with me?

547
00:25:54.063 --> 00:25:55.521
No. No, babe, it's not about you.

548
00:25:55.605 --> 00:25:57.896
No, when I say shitty life,
I'm mainly talking about my job.


549
00:25:57.980 --> 00:25:58.938
Ah.

550
00:26:00.563 --> 00:26:01.480
You work with me.

551
00:26:02.938 --> 00:26:05.688
Yeah. All I'm saying is
that perhaps I'll have a chance now


552
00:26:05.771 --> 00:26:07.771
to understand what I really want to do
with my life,


553
00:26:07.855 --> 00:26:09.855
without obsessing over money. Yeah?

554
00:26:09.938 --> 00:26:10.855
[Rocco] You're right.

555
00:26:10.938 --> 00:26:13.605
But maybe you should do it
regardless of the money.


556
00:26:13.688 --> 00:26:15.938
After all,
it's your parents' money, no? [chuckles]


557
00:26:16.021 --> 00:26:18.271
["Dancing in the Moonlight"
continues playing]


558
00:26:19.396 --> 00:26:20.896
-[turns off music]
-[Alessandra sighs]


559
00:26:22.271 --> 00:26:24.563
-Damn, honey!
-[sighs]


560
00:26:24.646 --> 00:26:27.063
Why the fuck couldn't you
just try and support me?


561
00:26:27.146 --> 00:26:28.896
