it was all a lie, though.


600
00:28:06.230 --> 00:28:07.855
They'll disappear from our lives forever.

601
00:28:07.938 --> 00:28:10.355
Hey, good riddance.
Those kids are such assholes.


602
00:28:10.438 --> 00:28:12.230
Yeah, I know, they really are.

603
00:28:12.313 --> 00:28:13.188
[tuts]

604
00:28:13.980 --> 00:28:16.396
At least we'll have Christmas together,
like you always wanted.


605
00:28:16.480 --> 00:28:20.105
Yes. All of us together
for one last Christmas.


606
00:28:20.188 --> 00:28:21.521
-[Carlo] Mm.
-[phone vibrates]


607
00:28:21.605 --> 00:28:22.688
[Carlo exhales]

608
00:28:23.396 --> 00:28:24.521
Ooh, ooh!

609
00:28:24.605 --> 00:28:25.980
A message from Emilio.

610
00:28:26.063 --> 00:28:29.813
-[gasps] "Mom and Dad, I really love you."
-Mm.


611
00:28:29.896 --> 00:28:33.313
-Oh, honey, you know that…
-That they're assholes.


612
00:28:33.396 --> 00:28:36.771
-Mm.
-Though… it still feels nice, you know?


613
00:28:37.355 --> 00:28:38.313
I mean…

614
00:28:38.980 --> 00:28:39.896
[sighs]

615
00:28:41.230 --> 00:28:44.438
But how can we make them believe
that we're millionaires now?


616
00:28:44.521 --> 00:28:46.688
Hey, don't worry, 
I have it planned out.

617
00:28:46.771 --> 00:28:48.605
-You do?
-Yeah, you'll see.


618
00:28:49.146 --> 00:28:50.646
["Heart Of Glass" by Blondie playing]

619
00:28:50.730 --> 00:28:52.730
What about this one here?

620
00:28:52.813 --> 00:28:54.980
-It's pretty flashy, huh?
-How about this one?


621
00:28:55.063 --> 00:28:56.021
-[chuckles]
-No, no.


622
00:28:57.230 --> 00:29:00.438
<i>♪ Once I had a love
and it was a gas ♪</i>

623
00:29:01.563 --> 00:29:04.438
