1185
00:55:24.855 --> 00:55:26.146
And how did he take it?

1186
00:55:26.230 --> 00:55:29.938
Well, we talked,
we found some common ground.


1187
00:55:30.021 --> 00:55:32.646
You know, we're all to blame
in this mess here, you know.


1188
00:55:32.730 --> 00:55:35.063
-Oh, yeah, yeah.
-He's the first to admit it, though.


1189
00:55:35.896 --> 00:55:38.355
And anyway,
I didn't tell him, in the end, that…


1190
00:55:38.438 --> 00:55:40.605
that the inheritance was a bullshit story.

1191
00:55:40.688 --> 00:55:42.480
-What do you mean?
-[Carlo] Well…


1192
00:55:42.563 --> 00:55:45.563
We talked about our relationship,
which is the most important thing. Uh…


1193
00:55:45.646 --> 00:55:47.105
Oh, well, it sure is, yeah.

1194
00:55:47.188 --> 00:55:49.438
And I promised him 200,000 euros,
to become a partner.


1195
00:55:49.521 --> 00:55:51.521
[thunder rumbling]

1196
00:55:52.480 --> 00:55:54.313
-Are you stupid?
-Huh?


1197
00:55:54.396 --> 00:55:56.605
Where are we getting 200,000 euros?

1198
00:55:58.605 --> 00:55:59.938
Well, fuck if I know!

1199
00:56:02.730 --> 00:56:05.646
Did you see Alessandra?
Did you manage to, uh, tell her?


1200
00:56:05.730 --> 00:56:07.605
Oh. Yes.

1201
00:56:07.688 --> 00:56:08.771
[Alessandra] Hi, Daddy.

1202
00:56:10.146 --> 00:56:10.980
[Carlo] Hi.

1203
00:56:11.063 --> 00:56:11.938
Is dinner ready?

1204
00:56:12.021 --> 00:56:13.313
[Anna] Well, almost.

1205
00:56:14.563 --> 00:56:17.355
Oh. We decided that I'll come back
and stay here with you. Oh.


1206
00:56:17.438 --> 00:56:18.980
-Ah.
-[Alessandra] Isn't that nice?


1207
00:56:19.063 --> 00:56:20.063
Yes.

1208
00:56:20.146 --> 00:56:23.146
Yeah, so I can help you figure out
what to do with all this money.


1209
00:56:23.230 --> 00:56:24.063
Yeah.

1210
00:56:24.146 --> 00:56:26.105
Mom is getting stressed about
being a millionaire.


1211
00:56:26.188 --> 00:56:27.563
It's too much for her. You know?

1212
00:56:27.646 --> 00:56:29.771
-She needs our support.
-Yes, we'll support her.


1213
00:56:29.855 --> 00:56:32.563
Too much money.
She's stressed out. She's stressed out.


1214
00:56:33.480 --> 00:56:35.480
[pleasant music playing]

1215
00:56:47.813 --> 00:56:51.980
Make sure you don't mention the…
the whole inheritance thing, okay?


1216
00:56:52.063 --> 00:56:53.063
Why not?

1217
00:56:53.146 --> 00:56:56.605
Why? Because when it comes to money,
people pounce on you and never let you go.


1218
00:56:56.688 --> 00:56:58.646
Especially relatives, you know.

1219
00:56:58.730 --> 00:57:00.105
[indistinct chatter]

1220
00:57:01.105 --> 00:57:03.646
Good evening. Here we are.

1221
00:57:03.730 --> 00:57:04.771
Good evening.

1222
00:57:05.271 --> 00:57:07.271
[laughing]

1223
00:57:08.480 --> 00:57:10.980
You're really sweet. 
Thank you, my dear.

1224
00:57:11.063 --> 00:57:14.521
I haven't seen everyone together
since the funeral, you know.


1225
00:57:15.355 --> 00:57:16.271
[glass clinking]

1226
00:57:16.355 --> 00:57:21.105
Excuse me. Excuse me. Uh…
I'd like to make a quick toast.


1227
00:57:21.188 --> 00:57:22.896
What a drag!

1228
00:57:22.980 --> 00:57:24.355
[Anna] Yes, exactly!

1229
00:57:24.438 --> 00:57:27.438
I had actually prepared
a very emotional speech,


1230
00:57:27.521 --> 00:57:30.021
but then,
given your notorious sentimentalism,


1231
00:57:30.105 --> 00:57:32.230
I thought, "Mom is
going to cry too much,"

1232
00:57:32.313 --> 00:57:34.021
so I've chosen to put that aside,

1233
00:57:34.105 --> 00:57:38.313
and I'm only going to tell you…
Mama, I really love you.


1234
00:57:38.396 --> 00:57:39.355
[all] Aw.

1235
00:57:39.438 --> 00:57:41.688
All the best,
and happy birthday, Giuliana!


1236
00:57:41.771 --> 00:57:42.855
-[applauding]
-Yes. Cheers!


1237
00:57:42.938 --> 00:57:46.771
-Happy birthday.
-Cheers, everyone, cheers to you!


1238
00:57:46.855 --> 00:57:48.521
[laughing]

1239
00:57:49.105 --> 00:57:52.355
-Anna. Anna.
-What's up, Matteo?


1240
00:57:53.480 --> 00:57:56.855
Anna, it seems that
you saved up all your most touching


1241
00:57:56.938 --> 00:57:59.896
and heartfelt words for my mother only.

1242
00:58:03.938 --> 00:58:06.771
Wha-- What's that?
Everyone here loved her deeply.


1243
00:58:06.855 --> 00:58:07.813
What are…

1244
00:58:08.605 --> 00:58:10.355
I mean, she left me barely any money.

1245
00:58:11.230 --> 00:58:13.771
-But here you are with your Ferrari.
-Uh… Uh…


1246
00:58:13.855 --> 00:58:15.313
Please don't do this, honey.

1247
00:58:16.021 --> 00:58:18.480
And anyway, where did she get it,
all that money?


1248
00:58:18.563 --> 00:58:20.771
Huh? Tell me that, at least.
Anna, tell me!


1249
00:58:20.855 --> 00:58:22.730
She must have got it from Bisacci.

1250
00:58:22.813 --> 00:58:25.105
If you hadn't objected to
her relationship with Bisacci…


1251
00:58:25.188 --> 00:58:28.521
But… What are you talking about?
Mom never had any kind of affair.


1252
00:58:28.605 --> 00:58:29.855
[exhales]

1253
00:58:29.938 --> 00:58:32.355
Plus, you weren't even
in the will, were you?


1254
00:58:32.438 --> 00:58:33.480
So what did you do?

1255
00:58:33.563 --> 00:58:34.896
What did you do, huh?

1256
00:58:34.980 --> 00:58:38.105
I mean, did you make her write
a private agreement on her deathbed?


1257
00:58:38.188 --> 00:58:39.188
-[people gasp]
-Carlo?


1258
00:58:39.271 --> 00:58:40.855
I… I've lost my napkin.

1259
00:58:40.938 --> 00:58:43.605
Uh, well, no, no, no, it's not
what you think, Matteo, sorry, okay?


1260
00:58:43.688 --> 00:58:46.105
-No?
-Oh, no? Then what is it?


1261
00:58:48.980 --> 00:58:50.230
[chair scraping on floor]

1262
00:58:51.855 --> 00:58:56.688
Anna must have sent over her husband.
Her husband did the dirty work.


1263
00:58:58.021 --> 00:59:01.480
First with that Bisacci, and then Carlo.

1264
00:59:01.563 --> 00:59:03.063
[people murmuring]

1265
00:59:03.146 --> 00:59:05.271
So then Carlo
was fucking her as well, yeah?


1266
00:59:05.355 --> 00:59:06.271
[people gasp]

1267
00:59:06.355 --> 00:59:08.438
What? Are you all crazy? 
Me and Bisacci?

1268
00:59:08.521 --> 00:59:11.396
Who the fuck is Bisacci?
Seriously, who's that? Huh?


1269
00:59:12.021 --> 00:59:12.855
Teo!

1270
00:59:12.938 --> 00:59:14.521
-[Teo] Where'd you put the money?
-See?


1271
00:59:14.605 --> 00:59:15.855
-Come on now, hold on!
-Whoa!


1272
00:59:15.938 --> 00:59:17.313
-[woman] He's gonna beat him.
-It's a party.


1273
00:59:17.396 --> 00:59:18.438
-Stop him!
-Teo!


1274
00:59:18.521 --> 00:59:20.313
-Move! Move!
-[Emilio] Stop this.


1275
00:59:20.396 --> 00:59:22.396
-[grunts]
-[all gasp]


1276
00:59:23.313 --> 00:59:25.521
[breathing heavily]

1277
00:59:25.605 --> 00:59:29.146
-[a cappella song playing]
-[dog barking in distance]


1278
00:59:30.230 --> 00:59:32.021
[Emilio] Nice and easy.

1279
00:59:32.105 --> 00:59:33.855
-I'm gonna sit there, okay?
-Yes.


1280
00:59:34.563 --> 00:59:35.938
[Carlo exhales]

1281
00:59:37.146 --> 00:59:39.188
[breathes deeply]

1282
00:59:39.813 --> 00:59:40.855
Okay.

1283
00:59:40.938 --> 00:59:43.438
-Ow, ow, ow, ow, ow, ow!
-Easy.


1284
00:59:43.521 --> 00:59:44.396
[exhales]

1285
00:59:44.480 --> 00:59:45.313
[inhales deeply]

1286
00:59:45.396 --> 00:59:46.355
[groans]

1287
00:59:47.188 --> 00:59:48.688
If I ever have a family,

1288
00:59:48.771 --> 00:59:51.396
I don't think I'll be able
to do all you've done for us.


1289
00:59:52.396 --> 00:59:55.605
You'll see, when you have your own family,
it will come natural to you. [laughs]


1290
00:59:55.688 --> 00:59:56.771
I don't know.

1291
00:59:56.855 --> 00:59:58.771
I'm not sure even six million dollars

1292
00:59:58.855 --> 01:00:02.105
would convince me
to sleep with Aunt Tea! [laughs]


1293
01:00:02.188 --> 01:00:03.646
What, so you're a moron, too?

1294
01:00:03.730 --> 01:00:05.521
-Unbelievable.
-[chuckles]


1295
01:00:05.605 --> 01:00:07.688
[Anna] Honey, how are you feeling?

1296
01:00:07.771 --> 01:00:11.271
-Like a train wreck.
-[Anna] No, please, don't play the victim.


1297
01:00:12.980 --> 01:00:15.188
-Are you decorating the tree?
-[Anna] Mm-hmm.


1298
01:00:18.730 --> 01:00:19.771
It's snowing out!

1299
01:00:19.855 --> 01:00:21.021
[happy music playing]

1300
01:00:21.105 --> 01:00:24.396
How nice. It hasn't snowed here in ages!

1301
01:00:24.480 --> 01:00:25.313
[gasps]

1302
01:00:25.396 --> 01:00:26.230
What? Snow?

1303
01:00:26.313 --> 01:00:28.230
-Yes.
-Fuck, I came on my moped.


1304
01:00:28.313 --> 01:00:31.063
Well, why don't you both just
spend the night here? Why not?


1305
01:00:31.146 --> 01:00:33.146
We'll decorate the tree together.

1306
01:00:35.105 --> 01:00:37.896
I'll make some hot chocolate
for all of us. With whipped cream.


1307
01:00:37.980 --> 01:00:39.730
-Hmm?
-Yeah. Why not? [chuckles]


1308
01:00:39.813 --> 01:00:40.813
[laughs]

1309
01:00:42.188 --> 01:00:43.021
Mm.

1310
01:00:46.688 --> 01:00:47.688
Mm.

1311
01:00:49.105 --> 01:00:51.438
-What is it? Huh?
-I'm so happy.


1312
01:00:51.980 --> 01:00:53.771
-[chuckles]
-[Emilio chuckles]


1313
01:00:54.688 --> 01:00:55.646
[Anna] Hmm.

1314
01:01:04.438 --> 01:01:06.688
[gasps] Oh, look at this one.

1315
01:01:06.771 --> 01:01:08.980
This jacket would be just perfect for her.

1316
01:01:09.063 --> 01:01:10.646
Okay, but how much is it?

1317
01:01:10.730 --> 01:01:14.188
[sighs] Would you please stop talking
about money?


1318
01:01:18.313 --> 01:01:19.896
Anyway, this thing has to stop.

1319
01:01:19.980 --> 01:01:22.438
I mean, we literally…
we just can't afford it anymore.


1320
01:01:22.521 --> 01:01:24.938
I know, we talked about it already.
Just until Christmas.


1321
01:01:25.021 --> 01:01:26.021
I know, but at this rate,

1322
01:01:26.105 --> 01:01:28.730
we'll have to start selling our organs
to survive until Christmas.


1323
01:01:29.271 --> 01:01:32.105
Stop being such a damn joy-killer!
I said just until Christmas.


1324
01:01:32.188 --> 01:01:33.980
Is that too much?
Is that too much for you?


1325
01:01:34.938 --> 01:01:36.563
You scare me, you know that?

1326
01:01:37.063 --> 01:01:38.896
Look at that one! [gasps]

1327
01:01:40.605 --> 01:01:43.813
Let's give them two vouchers
for a Caribbean holiday next summer.


1328
01:01:43.896 --> 01:01:45.480
It's pretty easy to get those vouchers.

1329
01:01:46.146 --> 01:01:48.938
It's a Versace. 
Should I get her this too?

1330
01:01:49.021 --> 01:01:50.438
So she can pair it.

1331
01:01:51.021 --> 01:01:53.021
Mm. Does Versace take vouchers?

1332
01:01:58.188 --> 01:02:01.230
How about this wrinkled one?
Maybe it's a little cheaper.


1333
01:02:02.146 --> 01:02:04.146
[cheerful music playing]

1334
01:02:11.063 --> 01:02:14.021
-What could come after five stars?
-Ah, bankruptcy.


1335
01:02:14.105 --> 01:02:15.230
Paradiso.

1336
01:02:23.063 --> 01:02:24.521
-Hey.
-Nice place here.


1337
01:02:24.605 --> 01:02:26.230
-Isn't it?
-[Carlo] Hey.


1338
01:02:32.646 --> 01:02:34.480
-How are you doing? Good?
-Fine.


1339
01:02:34.563 --> 01:02:35.563
-Good?
-Yes.


1340
01:02:36.313 --> 01:02:37.521
[sighs]

1341
01:02:37.605 --> 01:02:38.688
I made up with Rocco.

1342
01:02:38.771 --> 01:02:39.771
Ah!

1343
01:02:39.855 --> 01:02:41.605
My love, I'm so happy for you.

1344
01:02:41.688 --> 01:02:43.605
-Well, he's a wonderful guy.
-Yes.


1345
01:02:43.688 --> 01:02:46.105
We're not together, though.
We just made up.


1346
01:02:46.646 --> 01:02:49.688
Because I realized I
want to find my path.

1347
01:02:49.771 --> 01:02:52.313
I want to figure out
my dream, my ambitions.


1348
01:02:53.063 --> 01:02:53.980
What ambitions?

1349
01:02:55.230 --> 01:02:56.271
Mine.

1350
01:02:56.355 --> 01:02:58.396
Really? I didn't know.

1351
01:02:58.480 --> 01:03:00.105
Yes, I know you think I'm an idiot,

1352
01:03:00.188 --> 01:03:02.105
and that Emilio is the only one
who'll succeed.


1353
01:03:02.188 --> 01:03:03.938
-No.
-No, Emilio won't make it either.


1354
01:03:04.021 --> 01:03:05.438
-Hey, come on!
-[laughs]


1355
01:03:06.230 --> 01:03:07.105
Anyway.

1356
01:03:08.605 --> 01:03:10.688
I want to open a tea salon now.

1357
01:03:10.771 --> 01:03:13.480
Tea room and bookstore.
I've already found a spot!


1358
01:03:13.563 --> 01:03:14.646
Oh.

1359
01:03:14.730 --> 01:03:17.188
It's so wonderful to see you so excited
about something.


1360
01:03:17.271 --> 01:03:18.105
Very exciting.

1361
01:03:18.188 --> 01:03:19.980
Plus, I decided to
move out of your house.

1362
01:03:20.063 --> 01:03:23.730
I don't want to risk the quicksand effect,
getting too comfy and stuck there at home.


1363
01:03:23.813 --> 01:03:26.646
-I can understand that.
-No. No, but why? Uh…


1364
01:03:26.730 --> 01:03:29.063
Uh, well, but where will you go, anyway?

1365
01:03:29.146 --> 01:03:30.980
Well, here. I got a suite.

1366
01:03:32.605 --> 01:03:35.230
But it's so comfortable at home,
the three of us.


1367
01:03:35.313 --> 01:03:36.563
It's only for a couple of days.

1368
01:03:36.646 --> 01:03:39.480
I'm already looking for a small flat.
You know, something, uh…


1369
01:03:39.563 --> 01:03:42.355
And, well, I can pay for it
if you can help me.


1370
01:03:44.771 --> 01:03:46.480
Uh… Uh…

1371
01:03:47.105 --> 01:03:48.021
Uh…

1372
01:03:48.605 --> 01:03:50.688
Give me the checkbook, 
I'll sign one.

1373
01:03:50.771 --> 01:03:53.021
It's just that
I don't know if I have it on me.


1374
01:03:53.105 --> 01:03:55.480
-You always have it. Give it to me.
-But I changed my jacket.


1375
01:03:55.563 --> 01:03:56.521
Give it now.

1376
01:04:00.938 --> 01:04:02.896
-[chuckles] What luck, I have it!
-Told you.


1377
01:04:02.980 --> 01:04:03.980
[both chuckle]

1378
01:04:04.563 --> 01:04:06.105
[Carlo] I have a pen, too.

1379
01:04:06.188 --> 01:04:08.188
[Anna] Honey, how much do you need?

1380
01:04:08.271 --> 01:04:10.938
Well, you know, I need
to leave a deposit, so, uh…


1381
01:04:11.021 --> 01:04:12.230
You wanna buy the suite?

1382
01:04:12.938 --> 01:04:14.938
No, b-but for the tea salon.

1383
01:04:15.021 --> 01:04:15.896
[Carlo] Ah.

1384
01:04:16.396 --> 01:04:18.646
I don't know. Ten? 
Twenty thousand?

1385
01:04:18.730 --> 01:04:21.313
I know you gave 200,000 to Emilio, so…

1386
01:04:21.396 --> 01:04:24.188
-No, but it's just that… just that…
-No! We talked about it, but then…


1387
01:04:24.271 --> 01:04:26.188
-[laughs] …we didn't.
-Mm-hmm.


1388
01:04:26.271 --> 01:04:29.146
Forty? So I won't have to bother you
every single month


1389
01:04:29.230 --> 01:04:30.938
asking you for money transfers.

1390
01:04:31.480 --> 01:04:33.438
No, you're not bothering us at all.

1391
01:04:33.521 --> 01:04:37.021
In fact, if we spread it out,
we'll see more of each other. [chuckles]


1392
01:04:37.105 --> 01:04:39.313
[solemn music playing]

1393
01:04:40.646 --> 01:04:41.480
[sniffles]

1394
01:04:42.980 --> 01:04:43.813
Forty, then.

1395
01:04:44.646 --> 01:04:46.313
-Forty, yes.
-Yes.


1396
01:04:46.396 --> 01:04:47.271
Okay.

1397
01:04:51.855 --> 01:04:54.480
-It's missing a zero there.
-Mind your own business.


1398
01:04:56.521 --> 01:04:57.855
-[check ripping]
-There you go.


1399
01:04:59.021 --> 01:05:00.313
[chuckling] Thank you.

1400
01:05:00.896 --> 01:05:03.188
[whimsical music playing]

1401
01:05:05.396 --> 01:05:06.855
Careful, it's slippery.

1402
01:05:08.063 --> 01:05:09.605
Heels in the snow!

1403
01:05:11.063 --> 01:05:12.271
[coughs]

1404
01:05:12.355 --> 01:05:13.771
[man] Welcome!

1405
01:05:13.855 --> 01:05:16.563
I'm so glad you guys called me.
How have you been lately?


1406
01:05:16.646 --> 01:05:19.063
[chuckles] Not too bad. 
How are you doing?

1407
01:05:19.146 --> 01:05:22.105
Doing good, doing good. Please,
why don't you follow me to the parlor?


1408
01:05:22.188 --> 01:05:25.146
That way, we can talk more privately.
Please come this way.


1409
01:05:26.313 --> 01:05:28.480
I didn't know
there was a parlor. [chuckles]


1410
01:05:28.563 --> 01:05:30.980
Only for special clients,
you know? It's a secret.


1411
01:05:31.063 --> 01:05:33.188
-Like a Batcave?
-Exactly.


1412
01:05:33.271 --> 01:05:36.438
And you're the Bruce Wayne
of Speroncello. Yeah? Right?


1413
01:05:36.521 --> 01:05:38.105
[chuckles] This way.

1414
01:05:40.021 --> 01:05:41.938
I don't want to be disturbed
for half an hour.


1415
01:05:43.355 --> 01:05:45.730
-Parlor? It's his office.
-[man] Okay.


1416
01:05:48.605 --> 01:05:50.563
Okay then. What can
I do for you today?

1417
01:05:50.646 --> 01:05:54.146
Well, we'd like to cash in
our life insurance policy


1418
01:05:54.230 --> 01:05:56.230
and transfer it to our account.

1419
01:05:56.313 --> 01:05:58.605
And… And then? [chuckles]

1420
01:05:58.688 --> 01:06:01.396
And, uh, that's it.

1421
01:06:01.480 --> 01:06:04.605
Uh, and then we'd like to
empty out the account, too.


1422
01:06:06.855 --> 01:06:09.230
But… You… But why?

1423
01:06:12.480 --> 01:06:14.521
Well… It's a personal matter.

1424
01:06:18.480 --> 01:06:21.021
You're switching to
a big city bank, I imagine.


1425
01:06:21.105 --> 01:06:21.938
No.

1426
01:06:22.480 --> 01:06:25.355
Where you feel more comfortable,
you and your Ferrari.


1427
01:06:25.438 --> 01:06:27.313
But those banks don't know you.

1428
01:06:27.396 --> 01:06:31.188
You are small town folk,
coming from… from… from a place where…


1429
01:06:31.271 --> 01:06:32.646
where the air smells of manure.

1430
01:06:32.730 --> 01:06:33.813
Am I right?

1431
01:06:33.896 --> 01:06:35.605
What are you saying? 
Have you gone crazy?

1432
01:06:35.688 --> 01:06:39.521
Ditching us
after a trusted ten-year relationship?


1433
01:06:39.605 --> 01:06:42.105
What relationship?
But… But remember Sharm el-Sheikh?


1434
01:06:42.188 --> 01:06:44.146
When we had a credit limit,
I tried to raise it,


1435
01:06:44.230 --> 01:06:46.063
and you told me to fuck off.
What relationship?


1436
01:06:46.146 --> 01:06:48.605
Oh, no. I'm sorry,
sir, but that's a lie!

1437
01:06:48.688 --> 01:06:50.396
I couldn't even afford to buy henna there.

1438
01:06:50.480 --> 01:06:52.813
We had to spend
the rest of our vacation

1439
01:06:52.896 --> 01:06:55.396
cooped up in our room,
eating bread and falafel.


1440
01:06:55.480 --> 01:06:57.396
Bread and falafel. 
So good, though.

1441
01:06:57.480 --> 01:07:00.146
Well, I'm sorry,
but there are rules here, ma'am.


1442
01:07:00.230 --> 01:07:02.521
And rules must be respected! Okay?

1443
01:07:03.355 --> 01:07:06.563
No. And now you're gonna
give us our money,


1444
01:07:06.646 --> 01:07:10.188
because as a millionaire,
I won't be regulated. No rules at all.


1445
01:07:10.271 --> 01:07:13.105
And what's more, I can finally
tell you little bank people


1446
01:07:13.188 --> 01:07:14.646
to go fuck yourselves.

1447
01:07:17.188 --> 01:07:19.396
Oh. In fact… Look here.

1448
01:07:20.105 --> 01:07:23.646
Take this right here,
and go buy yourself a little class.


1449
01:07:23.730 --> 01:07:24.646
You boor.

1450
01:07:25.188 --> 01:07:26.646
I
-Isn't that too much?

1451
01:07:27.230 --> 01:07:28.605
[chuckles sheepishly] Forgive her.

1452
01:07:28.688 --> 01:07:30.896
She acts like that
because she's hot-blooded.


1453
01:07:30.980 --> 01:07:33.355
Two hundred euros.
You don't deserve a tip!


1454
01:07:33.438 --> 01:07:35.271
[laughs] Take… Take care.

1455
01:07:35.355 --> 01:07:38.105
Uh, Anna. We've made fools of ourselves!

1456
01:07:38.188 --> 01:07:39.896
[gentle music playing]

1457
01:07:39.980 --> 01:07:44.480
WE LOVE YOU… MOM AND DAD

1458
01:07:44.563 --> 01:07:45.896
[Carlo sighs] There.

1459
01:07:46.521 --> 01:07:48.188
All right. This is all we can do.

1460
01:07:48.271 --> 01:07:50.730
They'll have to forgive us
when we tell them the truth.


1461
01:07:50.813 --> 01:07:52.021
-You think?
-[Carlo] Jesus!


1462
01:07:52.105 --> 01:07:55.355
[chuckling] If I got 50,000 euros
for every time I was pranked,


1463
01:07:55.438 --> 01:07:57.271
I'd gladly be a laughingstock for life!

1464
01:07:57.355 --> 01:07:58.188
[Anna] Hmm.

1465
01:07:58.271 --> 01:07:59.396
[knocking on door]

1466
01:07:59.480 --> 01:08:00.521
Here they are.

1467
01:08:03.480 --> 01:08:05.521
I just bought the tea salon property!

1468
01:08:05.605 --> 01:08:08.063
-Huh?
-I just bought the tea salon property.


1469
01:08:08.688 --> 01:08:10.688
We're actually
signing the papers tomorrow.


1470
01:08:10.771 --> 01:08:11.896
Hello.

1471
01:08:11.980 --> 01:08:13.230
It was a real deal, you know?

1472
01:08:13.313 --> 01:08:15.521
Two hundred square meters
near the station.


1473
01:08:15.605 --> 01:08:16.813
And the real estate agent said

1474
01:08:16.896 --> 01:08:18.688
it's the most amazing bargain
he's ever seen.


1475
01:08:18.771 --> 01:08:19.605
-Uh…
-Oh, wow, cool.


1476
01:08:19.688 --> 01:08:21.105
Four hundred thousand euros!

1477
01:08:21.855 --> 01:08:23.980
[both] Oh.

1478
01:08:24.063 --> 01:08:27.521
After this, I promise I'll never
ask you for anything again. I swear.


1479
01:08:28.021 --> 01:08:30.980
And if you want to, you can give
the rest of my share to charity.


1480
01:08:31.063 --> 01:08:33.146
[chuckles] If she doesn't want her share,
I'll take it.


1481
01:08:33.230 --> 01:08:34.688
[all laugh]

1482
01:08:34.771 --> 01:08:36.021
-[Emilio] Dad, so…
-Yeah.


1483
01:08:36.105 --> 01:08:37.938
I have all the documents right here,

1484
01:08:38.021 --> 01:08:41.605
so we can get started on the paperwork
for the funding, okay?


1485
01:08:42.396 --> 01:08:44.021
What great news! [chuckles]

1486
01:08:44.521 --> 01:08:45.646
[Emilio] What's wrong?

1487
01:08:47.896 --> 01:08:50.188
-Mom, what's the matter?
-[inhales deeply]


1488
01:08:52.063 --> 01:08:54.980
Enough. We have to tell you the truth.

1489
01:08:56.480 --> 01:08:57.396
Uh…

1490
01:08:59.271 --> 01:09:01.355
Carlo. We have to.

1491
01:09:01.438 --> 01:09:03.605
-Tell them.
-[inhales deeply] Yes.


1492
01:09:04.146 --> 01:09:04.980
Tell us what?

1493
01:09:05.063 --> 01:09:06.355
Uh…

1494
01:09:10.396 --> 01:09:12.563
We can't give you any of the money.

1495
01:09:15.230 --> 01:09:16.063
There.

1496
01:09:17.355 --> 01:09:18.355
[Anna] Because…

1497
01:09:19.896 --> 01:09:22.063
[inhales deeply] Because your father…

1498
01:09:22.896 --> 01:09:24.230
Me? You, too!

1499
01:09:26.480 --> 01:09:27.855
…is very sick.

1500
01:09:29.188 --> 01:09:30.646
There. [sighs]

1501
01:09:30.730 --> 01:09:33.605
He has a terrible illness.
Really, really bad.


1502
01:09:36.938 --> 01:09:38.480
Is it a tumor?

1503
01:09:38.563 --> 01:09:40.396
[Anna] Ah. If only.

1504
01:09:40.480 --> 01:09:42.313
Yeah, holy shit.

1505
01:09:42.396 --> 01:09:44.271
-[Anna] It's a rare disease.
-[sighs]


1506
01:09:44.355 --> 01:09:47.605
And over in America,
they've been looking for a cure, and…


1507
01:09:48.563 --> 01:09:50.771
But the costs are extremely pricey.

1508
01:09:50.855 --> 01:09:51.938
Extremely pricey.

1509
01:09:52.521 --> 01:09:55.021
So, right now, financially, we have to…

1510
01:09:55.563 --> 01:09:57.146
concentrate our energy…

1511
01:09:57.730 --> 01:09:58.980
on saving your father now.

1512
01:09:59.063 --> 01:10:00.438
Save me, please.

1513
01:10:00.521 --> 01:10:03.813
But I don't get it.
What disease is it? What is it called?


1514
01:10:03.896 --> 01:10:04.730
-Uh…
-[Anna] Mm…


1515
01:10:04.813 --> 01:10:08.688
No, It doesn't have a name,
because they've only just discovered it.


1516
01:10:08.771 --> 01:10:11.146
-Yeah… discovered it.
-Sorry, but how did you realize?


1517
01:10:11.230 --> 01:10:14.646
[breathes deeply]

1518
01:10:14.730 --> 01:10:15.563
[Anna] Mm…

1519
01:10:15.646 --> 01:10:17.730
-I was feeling…
-[Anna] Yeah.


1520
01:10:17.813 --> 01:10:19.271
I was feeling weird.

1521
01:10:19.355 --> 01:10:20.730
You had vertigo.

1522
01:10:20.813 --> 01:10:24.313
Yes, but kind of counterclockwise.

1523
01:10:24.396 --> 01:10:27.646
And with these p-palpitations… [grunts]

1524
01:10:27.730 --> 01:10:28.688
…on and off.

1525
01:10:28.771 --> 01:10:31.521
Oh, st-- stop it,
it's just too disturbing.


1526
01:10:31.605 --> 01:10:32.438
[Carlo] Yeah.

1527
01:10:32.521 --> 01:10:34.230
Uh… Any-
- Anyway…

1528
01:10:34.313 --> 01:10:36.563
apart from the trip to see doctors
in America,


1529
01:10:36.646 --> 01:10:40.771
we plan on seeing doctors as well
in Paris and Tokyo.


1530
01:10:40.855 --> 01:10:42.521
Uh, and Hong Kong. 
Hong Kong too.

1531
01:10:42.605 --> 01:10:44.396
-[Carlo] They're top-notch.
-[Anna] Yes, yes.


1532
01:10:45.105 --> 01:10:48.188
Uh, but don't you worry,
because we'll be back by Christmas,


1533
01:10:48.271 --> 01:10:51.271
because Paris is only for two days,
and then we'll celebrate together.


1534
01:10:51.355 --> 01:10:53.646
-We'll be here for Christmas, no doubt.
-Yes.


1535
01:10:54.396 --> 01:10:56.271
All right. Anyway…

1536
01:10:57.188 --> 01:10:59.188
But this is all we can give you.

1537
01:10:59.271 --> 01:11:00.563
You're giving them money?

1538
01:11:02.980 --> 01:11:04.605
-Are you kidding?
-Huh?


1539
01:11:04.688 --> 01:11:05.563
[Anna] Hmm?

1540
01:11:07.021 --> 01:11:07.938
We don't want anything.

1541
01:11:12.313 --> 01:11:13.855
Thank you. Thank you.

1542
01:11:14.896 --> 01:11:15.938
Thank you.

1543
01:11:18.271 --> 01:11:19.105
Come here.

1544
01:11:19.188 --> 01:11:21.438
Let's all say a prayer for Dad now.

1545
01:11:21.938 --> 01:11:23.063
Yes, let's pray now.

1546
01:11:23.146 --> 01:11:24.396
[whispering] Drop dead!

1547
01:11:24.480 --> 01:11:26.230
[pleasant music playing]

1548
01:11:50.938 --> 01:11:53.563
-Now what? How you gonna fix this?
-[faucet running]


1549
01:11:53.646 --> 01:11:56.396
If you had a better idea,
you were free to express it.


1550
01:11:56.480 --> 01:11:58.521
Oh, an even better idea
than killing me off?


1551
01:11:58.605 --> 01:11:59.521
[turns off faucet]

1552
01:11:59.605 --> 01:12:02.063
No, I didn't know what to say.

1553
01:12:02.146 --> 01:12:05.105
-Quiet down, the kids are gonna hear us!
-[sighs]


1554
01:12:05.188 --> 01:12:07.105
Sooner or later they'll
realize I'm not dying.


1555
01:12:08.105 --> 01:12:09.355
Not necessarily.

1556
01:12:09.438 --> 01:12:12.980
So you want to kill me?
For one damn Christmas dinner?


1557
01:12:13.063 --> 01:12:15.813
Listen. We can just say
that you were cured,


1558
01:12:15.896 --> 01:12:18.021
or that the disease suddenly went dormant.

1559
01:12:18.105 --> 01:12:20.021
-[breathes deeply]
-[Carlo sighs]


1560
01:12:21.188 --> 01:12:23.021
-[grunting]
-[Anna exhales]


1561
01:12:23.980 --> 01:12:25.146
[knocking on door]

1562
01:12:25.230 --> 01:12:26.438
Who's that?

1563
01:12:29.771 --> 01:12:31.105
[Anna] My darlings.

1564
01:12:32.771 --> 01:12:33.855
Still awake?

1565
01:12:35.813 --> 01:12:38.188
Could we maybe sleep in the bed
with you tonight?


1566
01:12:40.521 --> 01:12:42.396
Like we did on Christmas
when we were little?


1567
01:12:42.480 --> 01:12:45.313
-Mm… Yes, of course.
-But we won't fit though.


1568
01:12:45.396 --> 01:12:46.480
Yes.

1569
01:12:49.855 --> 01:12:53.146
Well… let's just try and keep
our spirits up, okay?


1570
01:12:53.771 --> 01:12:57.855
Even though it may be the last Christmas
we spend together.


1571
01:12:57.938 --> 01:13:00.688
-Please!
-Aw, Mom, don't say that.


1572
01:13:01.355 --> 01:13:02.855
-Ouch! Hey!
-What?


1573
01:13:02.938 --> 01:13:04.605
I'm terminal and you
hit me? Come on! Huh?

1574
01:13:04.688 --> 01:13:06.355
-Sorry.
-Huh? Come on, now.


1575
01:13:06.438 --> 01:13:07.938
[Alessandra] Goodnight, Mom and Dad.

1576
01:13:08.021 --> 01:13:10.688
-Son, you need to shower, though.
-[Anna] Yes, yes, yes.


1577
01:13:10.771 --> 01:13:13.188
-Come on. It's unbearable, really.
-Here.


1578
01:13:13.271 --> 01:13:15.355
Don't pull the cover, leave it.

1579
01:13:15.438 --> 01:13:18.438
-Goodness! Like a sewer in Calcutta.
-Are you okay, there?


1580
01:13:18.521 --> 01:13:19.771
-[Carlo] Not the hand.
-Ah, good.


1581
01:13:19.855 --> 01:13:21.896
-Not the hand. I feel crushed!
-[Anna] No, don't--


1582
01:13:21.980 --> 01:13:24.146
Don't start stressing out.
It's bad for you.


1583
01:13:24.230 --> 01:13:26.480
-[Carlo] But I can't sleep like this.
-All right then.


1584
01:13:26.563 --> 01:13:28.355
-[Carlo sighs]
-Give me your hand, honey.


1585
01:13:28.438 --> 01:13:30.480
-[Carlo] My goodness.
-[Anna] Ah.


1586
01:13:30.563 --> 01:13:32.646
Let's sleep now. Come on.

1587
01:13:33.396 --> 01:13:35.355
Relax now. [breathes deeply]

1588
01:13:35.438 --> 01:13:37.396
[pleasant music playing]

1589
01:13:37.980 --> 01:13:40.063
[inaudible]

1590
01:13:42.438 --> 01:13:45.271
Okay. Perfect. Thank you.

1591
01:13:45.355 --> 01:13:46.730
-Thank you.
-[kid] Hi.


1592
01:13:46.813 --> 01:13:48.063
Hello!

1593
01:13:48.146 --> 01:13:49.605
-How are you?
-[kid] Fine.


1594
01:13:49.688 --> 01:13:51.480
Fine? What did you do today?

1595
01:13:51.563 --> 01:13:54.230
-[kid] I walked around.
-Oh.


1596
01:13:54.313 --> 01:13:56.230
-Okay. The doctor is waiting.
-Thank you.


1597
01:13:56.313 --> 01:13:58.063
-See you later. Bye-bye.
-[kid] Bye.


1598
01:13:58.146 --> 01:14:00.146
[music continues]

1599
01:14:14.313 --> 01:14:15.980
So, are you still living at home?

1600
01:14:16.063 --> 01:14:18.355
No, I'm staying now at Mara's.

1601
01:14:18.438 --> 01:14:22.396
I thought that it would be better
to leave Mom and Dad alone for a while.


1602
01:14:27.771 --> 01:14:29.230
[Rocco] How's your dad doing?

1603
01:14:29.855 --> 01:14:32.980
Well, he's… he's fine, for now,
thank goodness.


1604
01:14:33.521 --> 01:14:37.063
But I have the feeling that he's
putting on a brave face for us.


1605
01:14:38.230 --> 01:14:40.480
Anyway, now he's in Paris
for a consultation.


1606
01:14:40.563 --> 01:14:42.521
Well, I'd really like to see him sometime.

1607
01:14:43.230 --> 01:14:45.438
You know what?
Why don't we video call them now?


1608
01:14:45.521 --> 01:14:47.313
[Rocco] No, no, don't bother him now.

1609
01:14:47.396 --> 01:14:48.813
No, trust me. He'd like that.

1610
01:14:48.896 --> 01:14:50.688
Plus, I video call him,
like, ten times a day,


1611
01:14:50.771 --> 01:14:53.438
so at least, with you here,
you're giving me an excuse. Here.


1612
01:15:01.146 --> 01:15:03.271
-There they are. Ciao!
-[Rocco] Hello!


1613
01:15:03.355 --> 01:15:06.438
<i>-Hello!</i>
<i>-Hi, Rocco, how are things?</i>


1614
01:15:06.521 --> 01:15:09.521
-[Rocco] All good. Isn't Paris beautiful?
-Yes. A bit cold, though.


1615
01:15:09.605 --> 01:15:11.605
How come no one's around?

1616
01:15:11.688 --> 01:15:14.813
<i>Yeah, it's a bit quiet.</i>
<i>Listen, how are you? And Emilio?</i>


1617
01:15:16.063 --> 01:15:17.396
Ah. Um…

1618
01:15:17.480 --> 01:15:18.896
Didn't he tell you?

1619
01:15:18.980 --> 01:15:21.480
-[Carlo] <i>What's wrong?</i>
-Oh, he just got fired.


1620
01:15:21.563 --> 01:15:22.480
<i>But how come?</i>

1621
01:15:22.563 --> 01:15:25.355
Yeah, I don't think he wanted to tell you
right now, so you didn't worry,


1622
01:15:25.438 --> 01:15:28.313
but actually he's already looking
for another job, so…


1623
01:15:28.396 --> 01:15:30.230
Yes, in the meantime,
he's crashing at my place.


1624
01:15:30.313 --> 01:15:31.313
I'm… I'm putting him up.

1625
01:15:31.396 --> 01:15:33.396
I can't live
without a Delle Fave. [laughs]


1626
01:15:33.480 --> 01:15:34.438
<i>Let's call him now!</i>

1627
01:15:34.521 --> 01:15:37.396
[Alessandra] Seriously, Mom, don't worry.
Really, we're fine.


1628
01:15:38.688 --> 01:15:40.813
You enjoy Paris.

1629
01:15:41.688 --> 01:15:44.438
It's so nice to see you there,
so happy together.


1630
01:15:45.063 --> 01:15:46.855
<i>Come on, sweetheart, don't be like that.</i>

1631
01:15:46.938 --> 01:15:50.896
<i>Call him, please, so we can have</i>
<i>a little… a little family call.</i>


1632
01:15:50.980 --> 01:15:53.730
Sure thing. Wait, 
I'll try adding him now.

1633
01:15:56.605 --> 01:15:58.271
-Hey!
<i>-Hello!</i>


1634
01:15:58.355 --> 01:16:00.730
-[Anna] <i>Oh!</i>
-[Carlo] <i>Oh, you're all there.</i>[chuckles]


1635
01:16:00.813 --> 01:16:03.563
<i>-Hi. How's it going there?</i>
<i>-Fine, fine.</i>


1636
01:16:03.646 --> 01:16:05.605
<i>-I was just thinking about you.</i>
<i>-Mm.</i>


1637
01:16:05.688 --> 01:16:07.230
[Emilio] <i>Listen, uh, where are you?</i>

1638
01:16:07.313 --> 01:16:09.646
<i>I stopped by the house</i>
<i>to pick up a few shirts.</i>


1639
01:16:10.271 --> 01:16:11.105
<i>-Huh?</i>
<i>-Uh…</i>


1640
01:16:11.188 --> 01:16:15.230
Uh… Great. So w--
Okay, listen, we have to go.


1641
01:16:15.313 --> 01:16:16.438
[Alessandra] <i>No. Dad.</i>

1642
01:16:16.521 --> 01:16:19.271
-<i>Wait, how did it go with Dr. Rholande?</i>
-Good. Great.


1643
01:16:19.355 --> 01:16:21.146
<i>-Maybe I don't have shit.</i>
<i>-Exactly.</i>


1644
01:16:21.230 --> 01:16:23.230
What? You don't have shit? So, what?

1645
01:16:24.021 --> 01:16:25.646
<i>Bye. Bye now.</i>

1646
01:16:26.730 --> 01:16:27.646
Emilio?

1647
01:16:28.438 --> 01:16:29.730
What are you doing in Paris?

1648
01:16:33.188 --> 01:16:34.313
Bonjour.

1649
01:16:44.646 --> 01:16:46.730
-[Carlo exhales]
-[Anna sighs]


1650
01:16:47.646 --> 01:16:49.230
[Anna] You'd both vanished.

1651
01:16:49.730 --> 01:16:51.355
We never got to see you.

1652
01:16:52.313 --> 01:16:54.271
Your mother was desperate.

1653
01:16:54.355 --> 01:16:56.105
And you turned a blind eye.

1654
01:16:56.646 --> 01:16:58.855
Then, when you said
Christmas was called off,


1655
01:16:58.938 --> 01:17:01.313
you can imagine her reaction.
She was distraught.


1656
01:17:01.396 --> 01:17:03.188
By the way, it was all his idea.

1657
01:17:03.271 --> 01:17:04.896
But you didn't object to it.

1658
01:17:06.105 --> 01:17:09.396
Anyway… [chuckles]
…it started out as a game.


1659
01:17:09.938 --> 01:17:11.480
-Oh, a game, huh?
-[Carlo] Yeah.


1660
01:17:12.063 --> 01:17:14.980
"Uh, wanna bet they'll come back to us
if we have money?"


1661
01:17:15.063 --> 01:17:16.271
Well, you did come back!

1662
01:17:19.771 --> 01:17:21.980
We were planning to tell you
after Christmas.


1663
01:17:22.855 --> 01:17:24.813
It was just so nice having you here.

1664
01:17:24.896 --> 01:17:27.646
What about Dad's illness?
Was that a game, too?


1665
01:17:27.730 --> 01:17:30.230
[laughs] Well, yeah, thank God!

1666
01:17:30.313 --> 01:17:32.730
Uh, but it was your mom
who made that shit up.


1667
01:17:32.813 --> 01:17:34.771
Well, because Mom didn't know
what else to say.


1668
01:17:34.855 --> 01:17:37.646
Okay, but in the meantime,
it really fucked up our lives.


1669
01:17:37.730 --> 01:17:39.313
For real, shame on you two.

1670
01:17:39.396 --> 01:17:41.896
-Well, come on, we only wanted to--
-To what?


1671
01:17:41.980 --> 01:17:43.938
To feel that you were still around.

1672
01:17:50.480 --> 01:17:52.063
[Emilio] Have a nice Christmas.

1673
01:17:55.105 --> 01:17:57.105
-[somber music playing]
-[sighs]


1674
01:18:01.813 --> 01:18:02.646
Anna.

1675
01:18:03.605 --> 01:18:04.855
Don't be sad.

1676
01:18:04.938 --> 01:18:07.355
They'll be back, you know.
Where can they go?


1677
01:18:07.438 --> 01:18:09.438
[music continues]

1678
01:18:17.271 --> 01:18:20.105
At least now you have
a new purse from Versace.


1679
01:18:20.646 --> 01:18:21.521
Indeed.

1680
01:18:23.563 --> 01:18:24.438
[Emilio exhales]

1681
01:18:25.105 --> 01:18:28.605
I didn't even get to drive the Ferrari
around town. Not even once.


1682
01:18:29.605 --> 01:18:32.313
Sorry, Grandma, but why didn't
you tell us anything either?


1683
01:18:32.396 --> 01:18:34.230
God forbid I do that!

1684
01:18:34.313 --> 01:18:37.188
Never butt in on other's
personal business, especially family's.


1685
01:18:37.730 --> 01:18:40.021
-You are family.
-Yes, true. All the more reason.


1686
01:18:40.646 --> 01:18:41.938
Meanwhile, I lost my job.

1687
01:18:42.021 --> 01:18:44.563
Come on,
you were dying to get out of there.


1688
01:18:44.646 --> 01:18:46.605
When you think about it,
you're to blame, partly.


1689
01:18:46.688 --> 01:18:47.938
But mostly, they are.

1690
01:18:48.021 --> 01:18:49.771
Exactly. Thanks for that.

1691
01:18:49.855 --> 01:18:50.896
[exhales] Meaning?

1692
01:18:50.980 --> 01:18:53.646
Meaning, that I never would
have wanted to admit


1693
01:18:53.730 --> 01:18:57.521
that they would actually have
to pay for your affection. [chuckles]


1694
01:18:59.813 --> 01:19:03.105
They needed you so badly
that in the end they were willing


1695
01:19:03.188 --> 01:19:06.605
to ignore your indifference
and frequent cold shoulders.


1696
01:19:12.646 --> 01:19:13.521
Thank you.

1697
01:19:13.605 --> 01:19:16.688
No, no, no, no, leave it. Let me pay.

1698
01:19:16.771 --> 01:19:19.563
-No, please, Grandma. Let me.
-[Giuliana] I'll pay for it.


1699
01:19:19.646 --> 01:19:22.355
With all the money
I got from Aunt Tea…

1700
01:19:23.146 --> 01:19:24.938
I could buy out this restaurant.

1701
01:19:27.813 --> 01:19:29.438
Merry Christmas.

1702
01:19:29.521 --> 01:19:32.230
[gentle music playing]

1703
01:19:32.313 --> 01:19:33.271
[lights buzzing]

1704
01:19:45.646 --> 01:19:46.563
[lighter clicks]

1705
01:19:54.813 --> 01:19:55.688
Hi.

1706
01:19:56.355 --> 01:19:57.188
Hi.

1707
01:19:58.855 --> 01:20:00.480
So, you're already taking them down?

1708
01:20:01.021 --> 01:20:02.355
Huh? Uh…

1709
01:20:03.188 --> 01:20:07.271
Yes. Because now that
we're no longer millionaires,


1710
01:20:07.855 --> 01:20:09.563
we need to save on electricity.

1711
01:20:09.646 --> 01:20:14.605
Oh. Yes, I heard about the…
that prank of yours.


1712
01:20:17.146 --> 01:20:19.855
Well, not really a prank. Let's say…

1713
01:20:20.688 --> 01:20:25.438
it was more like a desperate attempt
to get attention from my children.


1714
01:20:27.063 --> 01:20:29.813
[sniffles] I'm so sorry.

1715
01:20:29.896 --> 01:20:31.896
-[people cheering]
-[bottle pops open]


1716
01:20:35.646 --> 01:20:37.063
How's your family doing?

1717
01:20:38.105 --> 01:20:41.896
I came out to smoke a cigarette,
but I really just wanted a break.


1718
01:20:42.605 --> 01:20:44.813
Can you hear all that
racket they're making?


1719
01:20:46.313 --> 01:20:49.855
[sighs] And my daughter-in-law is
unbearable and can't cook for shit!


1720
01:20:50.646 --> 01:20:51.855
[chuckles]

1721
01:20:53.521 --> 01:20:55.313
Well, merry Christmas, then.

1722
01:20:56.521 --> 01:20:57.563
Merry Christmas.

1723
01:21:01.105 --> 01:21:03.105
[joyful music playing]

1724
01:21:25.980 --> 01:21:26.980
[engine turns off]

1725
01:21:28.730 --> 01:21:30.438
[dog barking in distance]

1726
01:21:38.146 --> 01:21:39.896
Can't you wait till tomorrow?

1727
01:21:39.980 --> 01:21:41.896
How come? What do you care?

1728
01:21:41.980 --> 01:21:43.521
-It's Christmas Eve.
-[clicks tongue]


1729
01:21:43.605 --> 01:21:45.605
[Carlo sighs]

1730
01:21:48.563 --> 01:21:50.980
Listen, why don't we go
to the beach for a few days?


1731
01:21:51.563 --> 01:21:53.396
No, it's too damp there.

1732
01:21:55.563 --> 01:21:56.521
[Carlo sighs]

1733
01:21:57.438 --> 01:21:59.271
How about Paris? Huh?

1734
01:21:59.855 --> 01:22:00.730
[chuckles]

1735
01:22:00.813 --> 01:22:04.355
Since we still have that consultation
with the oncologist, Dr. Rholande!


1736
01:22:04.438 --> 01:22:07.438
-Mm. He's fallen terminally ill.
-Him too?


1737
01:22:07.521 --> 01:22:09.688
-There's an outbreak.
-Are you obsessed or what?


1738
01:22:09.771 --> 01:22:11.563
-[door latch clicks]
-Hey. What was that?


1739
01:22:11.646 --> 01:22:13.438
What? What is it?

1740
01:22:15.146 --> 01:22:18.480
-Must be Santa. Better put out the fire.
-[Anna] Hold on, hold on.


1741
01:22:18.563 --> 01:22:21.271
-Did you hear that? Hey, who is it?
-Who's there?


1742
01:22:22.146 --> 01:22:23.980
-[footsteps treading]
-[breathing shakily]


1743
01:22:24.063 --> 01:22:25.105
Who's there?

1744
01:22:27.521 --> 01:22:28.646
[Anna] Someone's here.

1745
01:22:29.605 --> 01:22:32.105
No, what was… No, no. 
No, you come here.

1746
01:22:32.188 --> 01:22:33.896
No. Where are you going?

1747
01:22:33.980 --> 01:22:36.188
Just come here. Come here.

1748
01:22:38.855 --> 01:22:40.105
[switch clicks]

1749
01:22:40.188 --> 01:22:41.605
-[Emilio] Merry Ch--
-[stoker clangs]


1750
01:22:41.688 --> 01:22:43.646
-[body thuds]
-[Alessandra] Dad, what're you doing?


1751
01:22:43.730 --> 01:22:44.730
Are you crazy?

1752
01:22:45.480 --> 01:22:48.188
Honey, did your father
knock out the same teeth?


1753
01:22:48.271 --> 01:22:50.813
-Come on.
-Some ice should fix it.


1754
01:22:52.646 --> 01:22:54.438
First a golf club, now a stoker.

1755
01:22:54.521 --> 01:22:56.313
Hey, maybe next time
you should, I don't know,


1756
01:22:56.396 --> 01:22:57.771
shoot me in the face instead, huh?

1757
01:22:57.855 --> 01:23:00.355
You snuck into the house
like a thief! Come on.


1758
01:23:00.438 --> 01:23:02.855
A thief? With sparklers in their hands!

1759
01:23:02.938 --> 01:23:05.438
How would I know?
First I see a glare, then a…


1760
01:23:05.521 --> 01:23:07.105
then a stranger's face,

1761
01:23:07.188 --> 01:23:11.021
a dick face with the… the satanic sneer,
so I struck you.


1762
01:23:11.105 --> 01:23:13.063
It's basic survival instinct, you know?

1763
01:23:13.146 --> 01:23:17.105
Let's just say, this Christmas seems
to have brought out the worst in us all.


1764
01:23:17.188 --> 01:23:18.105
Yeah.

1765
01:23:18.938 --> 01:23:23.271
But now we're… we're all here,
the four of us together.


1766
01:23:23.355 --> 01:23:25.480
Honey, try to smile.

1767
01:23:25.563 --> 01:23:26.605
[groans]

1768
01:23:26.688 --> 01:23:27.938
[Anna] Oh, well, never mind.

1769
01:23:28.646 --> 01:23:31.771
Even if I can't stand you,
I love you both.


1770
01:23:32.271 --> 01:23:34.730
You know, it's nice to hear it,
once in a while, huh?


1771
01:23:34.813 --> 01:23:36.646
["Christmas (Baby Please Come Home)"
playing]


1772
01:23:39.396 --> 01:23:41.146
Hey, remember this one?

1773
01:23:41.230 --> 01:23:44.480
When you were children,
I'd play this song and, uh,


1774
01:23:44.563 --> 01:23:48.271
we'd go around the house
on a treasure hunt for Christmas gifts.


1775
01:23:48.355 --> 01:23:51.355
Now we can hunt for my two teeth.
Who knows where they are.


1776
01:23:51.438 --> 01:23:53.271
What did you lose, a molar?

1777
01:23:53.355 --> 01:23:55.105
How the fuck do I know?

1778
01:23:55.188 --> 01:23:57.188
No need to get all pissy with me.

1779
01:23:57.271 --> 01:23:59.480
It's… It's Christmas.

1780
01:23:59.563 --> 01:24:01.063
It's Christmas.

1781
01:24:01.146 --> 01:24:02.646
[song continues]

1782
01:24:03.230 --> 01:24:05.063
[laughs]

1783
01:24:05.146 --> 01:24:07.938
[all laugh]

1784
01:24:08.021 --> 01:24:10.396
This rug has really never been cleaned.

1785
01:24:10.480 --> 01:24:12.480
Gross, it's covered in stains.

1786
01:24:13.980 --> 01:24:17.105
-So, what do they look like?
-They're teeth! They look like teeth!


1787
01:24:17.188 --> 01:24:19.605
-[Alessandra] But are they white?
-Not really.


1788
01:24:21.105 --> 01:24:24.480
<i>♪ They're singing "Deck the Halls" ♪</i>

1789
01:24:25.021 --> 01:24:28.646
<i>♪ But it's not like Christmas at all ♪</i>

1790
01:24:28.730 --> 01:24:32.396
<i>♪ 'Cause I remember when you were here ♪</i>

1791
01:24:32.480 --> 01:24:35.855
<i>♪ And all the fun we had last year ♪</i>

1792
01:24:35.938 --> 01:24:37.063
<i>♪ Christmas ♪</i>

1793
01:24:37.146 --> 01:24:39.313
<i>♪ Pretty lights on the tree</i>…<i>♪</i>

1794
01:24:39.396 --> 01:24:40.646
What did you lose, a molar?

1795
01:24:40.730 --> 01:24:42.230
How the fuck do I know?

1796
01:24:42.313 --> 01:24:45.313
-Look for them.
-[all laugh]


1797
01:24:45.855 --> 01:24:48.188
-[Alessandra] How did you realize?
-Uh<i>…</i>


1798
01:24:48.271 --> 01:24:49.521
I was feeling weird.

1799
01:24:49.605 --> 01:24:51.980
-[Anna] You… You had vertigo.
-[all laugh]


1800
01:24:53.938 --> 01:24:55.355
Fuck, this one's laughing.

1801
01:24:56.105 --> 01:24:58.730
-[Carlo] His name's Emilio, not Carlo.
-[Anna] Your name's Carlo.


1802
01:24:58.813 --> 01:25:01.688
So, your sister wants to at midnight
and not noon.


1803
01:25:01.771 --> 01:25:02.688
Let's do it again.

1804
01:25:02.771 --> 01:25:04.563
-It's been… years.
-We are!


1805
01:25:05.396 --> 01:25:08.146
[laughs] Weren't you supposed to talk?

1806
01:25:08.230 --> 01:25:09.813
It's so soft. Wanna touch it?

1807
01:25:09.896 --> 01:25:11.188
-Anna.
-Oh yeah.


1808
01:25:11.271 --> 01:25:12.563
-You look very pretty. Wow.
-Yeah.


1809
01:25:12.646 --> 01:25:14.271
[Anna] Yeah, but we haven't said shit yet.

1810
01:25:14.355 --> 01:25:16.313
Oh, no, I got it all wrong. 
My bad, sorry.

1811
01:25:17.230 --> 01:25:19.563
[laughing]

1812
01:25:19.646 --> 01:25:21.146
I knew it. I knew it.

1813
01:25:21.688 --> 01:25:22.896
[exhales loudly]

1814
01:25:23.605 --> 01:25:25.188
[all laugh]

1815
01:25:25.271 --> 01:25:26.396
Racco fixed your teeth?

1816
01:25:26.480 --> 01:25:28.938
-[blows raspberry]
-You were gonna say something else.


1817
01:25:29.021 --> 01:25:30.105
♪ <i>Christmas</i>♪

1818
01:25:30.188 --> 01:25:32.688
♪<i>But it's Christmas day </i>♪

1819
01:25:32.771 --> 01:25:34.313
♪<i>Please </i>♪
♪<i>Please </i>♪


1820
01:25:34.396 --> 01:25:35.230
♪ <i>Please…</i>♪

1821
01:25:35.313 --> 01:25:37.688
-[man] Okay, let's try that again--
-And now we're at the end.


1822
01:25:37.771 --> 01:25:39.396
[all laugh]

1823
01:25:39.480 --> 01:25:40.480
♪<i>Please </i>♪
♪<i>Please </i>♪


1824
01:25:40.563 --> 01:25:43.855
-♪ <i>Baby, please come home </i>♪
♪<i>Christmas </i>♪


1825
01:25:43.938 --> 01:25:47.730
♪<i>Baby, please come home </i>♪
♪ <i>Christmas</i>♪


1826
01:25:47.813 --> 01:25:49.605
♪ <i>Please come home </i>♪

1827
01:25:49.688 --> 01:25:50.771
[song fades]

1828
01:25:50.855 --> 01:25:52.855
[happy instrumental music playing]

1829
01:28:21.271 --> 01:28:23.105
[music ends]